{"_id":"OqqlCMgDTNL7DhGk","name":"I Will Stay with You Always","pages":[{"_id":"2q8SsghTKOQM4Qg1","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>I Will Stay with You Always</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> The Broken Ones</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 163-175.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/i-will-stay-with-you-always-p163-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735097,"modifiedTime":1781513735097,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"k03UNPaHnOx3II3D","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Will Stay with You Always - Setup</h2><p>162<br>Once upon a time…<br>Prague is a great city recovering from war, after <br>Fredrick the Great’s recently failed siege. Ostromir <br>Malý, the Bohemian regent of Prague, has sent <br>an urgent request for help to the Order. The <br>nobles charged with rebuilding Prague are being <br>murdered in a way that has shocked the city, one <br>each night and all by the same hand. Each corpse <br>has been found with a body part removed and a <br>message scrawled on the walls reading, “I will stay <br>with you always. ” Ostromir has commissioned <br>the well-known alchemist Konstantin Svoboda to <br>construct a new guardian for the city – a Golem <br>– but the construction has been delayed. Until <br>its completion, the Hunters have been called on <br>to track down the noble-stalking killer, while the <br>commoners of the city, enthralled, watch like the <br>audience at a play.<br>A Scenario Inspired by The <br>Happy Prince (Oscar Wilde) by <br>Tommaso De Benetti<br>I Will Stay with You Always<br>Safety Keywords:<br>  <br>Body Horror / Murder / Torture</p><p>163<br>The story that led us here…<br>In the city of Prague stood a statue called the Happy <br>Prince, so-called for its extraordinary beauty: the body of <br>the statue was covered with a thin layer of gold and the eyes <br>were sapphires. On the hilt of the sword are set beautiful <br>rubies. One quiet evening, a young swallow on his yearly <br>migration to Egypt decided to rest under the sculpture. The <br>Prince saw the way the ordinary people of Prague suffered <br>from hunger and fear in the half-ruined city, and the statue <br>wept with pity. The Prince’s tears moved the bird to feel <br>the same compassion for the commoners of the city. The <br>Prince convinced the swallow to take the precious things <br>from his body and bring them to those in need. “The living <br>think that gold can make them happy, ” said the Prince, and <br>on hearing that, the swallow consented. Day after day the <br>swallow stripped the statue of everything that was valuable <br>to give that wealth to the people of Prague, who were <br>ground endlessly beneath the bootheels of the powerful. <br>Doing so, however, took so long that winter arrived. The <br>swallow could no longer reach Egypt to be reunited with <br>his flock. He decided to stay near to the Prince, who the <br>bird now loved, until one sad day the cold froze the swallow <br>into a grim little statue. Being powerless to save his friend <br>finally broke the Prince’s heart. Now worthless, the statue <br>was removed and handed over to Konstantin Svoboda, the <br>alchemist, for his experiments. For some reason, the lump <br>of lead at the statue’s heart refused to melt.<br>At the request of God Himself, an angel descended from <br>Paradise to retrieve the two most precious things Prague <br>had to offer: the Prince’s heart and the body of the <br>swallow. But the angel returned to Heaven empty-<br>handed, for in both the heart of the Prince and the spirit <br>of the swallow pity had been replaced by hatred for the <br>way Prague had rewarded their generosity.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Deemed unworthy of Paradise, the spirit of the swallow <br>instead possessed the body of Alexandr Pták, known <br>professionally as Alexandr the Bird. He was a circus <br>acrobat whose trademark was long flights through the <br>air during the dangerous stunts that made up his act. <br>Alexandr, who officially disappeared a few weeks ago, is <br>now almost completely under the control of the spirit. <br>With the little lucidity he had left, the acrobat returned <br>to Černobog, the young son of a seamstress to whom <br>the swallow had donated two rubies. Černobog’s mother <br>died from hardship and deprivation she suffered in <br>making a noble’s party dress. The boy had long been <br>considering retaliation against the client who had made <br>such unreasonable demands. Černobog and Alexandr <br>overcame their communication barriers to reach an <br>agreement. First they would recover the Prince’s body <br>and then they would dedicate themselves to avenging his <br>memory. They arrived at the laboratory of Konstantin, <br>the alchemist in charge of building the Golem. <br>Konstantin was desperate. Despite all the resources that <br>had been provided to him, the work couldn’t proceed <br>without the essential missing ingredient, which is, <br>unfortunately for him, human flesh. The regent had <br>threatened to expel him from Prague in the absence of <br>developments, but the arrival of Černobog and Alexandr <br>seemed providential.</p><p>1<br>164<br>Although Černobog had been ready to pay for it with a <br>ruby, the Prince’s body had already been melted down. <br>His lead heart, however, is still relatively intact. Konstantin <br>thus proposes a pact: Černobog will invest the ruby to buy <br>the old circus from which Alexandr comes, which will <br>become the new secret laboratory of the alchemist. Then <br>the boy and Alexandr will be able to devote themselves <br>to their revenge, each time taking a piece of the body of <br>the victims as part of their bargain with the alchemist. In <br>return, Konstantin will rebuild the Prince, unleashing him <br>during the upcoming dance at Prague Castle...<br>Note: This Scenario presents an investigation in which <br>Hunters have a wide range of options on how to proceed. <br>The initial presentation of the places corresponds to the <br>Read aloud to the Hunters of the Scene Tree mode. This <br>method makes it easier for Hunters to review the clues and <br>overall situation at the beginning of each Scene.</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735098,"modifiedTime":1781513735098,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"obu6KrzrlBEMp4T4","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Will Stay with You Always - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The regent of Prague, <br>Ostromir Malý, welcomes you in his brightly lit study, located <br>inside the castle of the city, a fortified complex recently <br>renovated by Empress Maria Theresa of Habsburg. Behind his <br>slick desk of fine wood, the short, ragged little Ostromir almost <br>disappears. He welcomes you with a certain enthusiasm and <br>you immediately notice how nervous he is: after introducing <br>himself he begins to compulsively clean his glasses, while <br>trying in vain to attract the attention of two servants in order <br>to offer you refreshment. Without even letting you speak, <br>he tries to fill the silences with bizarre questions about the <br>nature of the Order, but he doesn’t seem really interested in <br>your answers. Around a marble table, seated on chairs lined <br>with red satin, there are three other people: an old man with <br>a long beard and gray mustache, a gentleman in his forties <br>with thick brown hair, and a gorgeous blonde girl in elegant <br>clothes. Ostromir introduces them respectively as Konstantin <br>Svoboda, a well-known alchemist, Bartoloměj Novotný, <br>assistant to the director of the National Theater, and Beáta <br>Czernin, a member of one of the noble families of the city.  <br>He then invites you to sit on empty chairs and, sinking into <br>his, begins to explain the situation.         <br>Place: A beautiful room in Prague Castle, too big for a <br>modest presence like that of Ostromir. In addition to the <br>table where much of the conversation will take place after <br>the arrival of the Hunters, there’s a beautiful display of <br>golden chandeliers hanging from the ceiling, large mirrors <br>with precious frames, fine carpets on polished floors, and, <br>on the walls, huge tapestries darkened by time. <br>Time: Late afternoon, an ideal time for tea.</p><p>165<br>Initial Situation: Ostromir appears obviously nervous as <br>if he knows how much his success depends on the Hunters’ <br>help. <br>Information: From the interview with Ostromir, <br>Konstantin, Bartoloměj, and Beáta, the following <br>information can be obtained:<br> ◆ Someone is killing (or trying to kill) prominent <br>people in Prague. The connection between the cases is <br>obvious, as the words “I will stay with you always” have <br>been found written on the wall with various substances <br>at the crime scenes. <br> ◆ Beáta found her murdered lover in her rooms, wearing <br>a dress he’ d bought for her. He was found missing an <br>arm.<br> ◆ Bartoloměj found the theater director, Gabriel Černý, <br>lying with one leg severed on the stage where a new <br>show was to be performed just a few hours later. <br> ◆ Konstantin seems to have escaped the killer through <br>a coincidental routine change (he had been delayed <br>longer than usual in a nearby tavern), but his alchemical <br>lab was devastated.<br>Hunters can now choose where to start their investigations.<br>Ostromir Malý<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria <br>Theresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the <br>palm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my <br>life, though so far the noble families support my authority.<br>Agenda: Capture the assassin who is causing panic among <br>the nobles / Avoid a popular uprising.<br>Beáta Czernin the Noblewoman<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage <br>of it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly <br>cause annoyances. <br>Agenda: Distancing myself from my late lover Danek in the <br>eyes of my husband and family / Finding out which monster <br>may have murdered him in this way.<br>The Alchemical <br>Laboratory<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You reach the workshop <br>from a small staircase on one side of Haštalská, the street <br>in Prague that runs alongside the Church of St. Castulus. A <br>stone corridor leads you to what looks like the entrance to <br>a cell, protected by a wooden door reinforced by large iron <br>bars. Konstantin pulls out a large key that he hangs on his <br>neck and makes his way inside the laboratory, where the <br>soft light of lanterns hanging on the wall illuminates a cold <br>space similar to a tomb. Built of red brick and furnished with <br>wooden tables and benches, the workshop houses hundreds <br>of stills, bottles, and parchments abandoned on dusty shelves. <br>Dried plants and other esoteric trinkets hang from the ceiling. <br>In the center of the room is a forge, which Konstantin uses <br>to process minerals of various kinds, while in the corner an <br>elegant wooden desk is covered with paperwork, inks, and <br>pens for writing. What strikes you most is the almost total <br>devastation of a wing of the laboratory, now a pile of rubble, <br>glass, and split wooden boards. On the ground, a dry puddle <br>of god-knows-what emits a nauseating stench. Konstantin</p><p>166<br>apologizes for the mess, saying he didn’t have the strength to <br>fix it, “now that he’s alone. ” On the wall, written in smears <br>with dark mineral powders, you see: “I will stay with you <br>always. ” <br>Descriptor: An underground laboratory with a large forge <br>and esoteric trinkets. The east wing is a pile of rubble and on <br>the wall in front of you can clearly be read the phrase: “I will <br>stay with you always.”<br>Information: Depending on their ability to ask questions <br>and examine clues, Hunters can access some or all of the <br>following information:<br> ◆ Anything that was broken or stolen had little value, <br>with the exception of a lead heart that belonged to an <br>old statue that was recently removed from the city. <br>Konstantin says that the heart was the subject of his <br>studies, as he had not been able to melt it. <br> ◆ Konstantin is working on a secret project on behalf <br>of the city of Prague (the Golem), which he is very <br>reluctant to talk about. Apparently, it’s not proceeding <br>as planned. <br> ◆ A few days ago, a man who was in charge of cleaning <br>was fired: Georg Slanina, who lives in the nearby <br>rookery. Konstantin claims he was often intoxicated, <br>which is true. The real reason for the dismissal, not to be <br>revealed to the Hunters directly, was to allow Alexandr <br>to recover the Prince’s heart and stage the devastation <br>of the laboratory without inconvenient witnesses.<br>Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am one of the most prominent alchemists in <br>Prague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me. <br>Agenda: Create a Golem thanks to my alchemical studies <br>and prove that no noble title or institutional position can <br>possibly compare to my alchemical knowledge. <br>Gift – The Secrets of Metal:  Konstantin knows arcane <br>words that allow him to control metal. Any action against <br>him involving a metal weapon or bludgeoning tool receives <br>1 Penalty. Starting from moderate amounts of raw materials, <br>Konstantin can also forge various metal objects with <br>unusual properties. The Storyteller must create a Descriptor <br>that outlines this property (for example: The alloy of this <br>dagger violently repels other metals). <br>Gift – The Secrets of Flesh:  Once per Scene, when a <br>metallic body is in the vicinity of warm flesh, whether it’s still <br>attached to the body or only recently removed, Konstantin <br>can utter some arcane words, forcing the two elements to <br>merge. The procedure causes 1 immediate Wound, and 1 <br>additional Wound during the painful medical procedure <br>necessary to untangle flesh and metal.</p><p>167<br>The Rookery<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  As you enter the rookery, <br>you realize that you are being spied on: tired and hostile faces <br>observe you from half-open balconies; mothers hurriedly pick <br>up the children playing in the street and the men spit on the <br>ground when they pass you by. On several street corners, you <br>notice men and women in brightly colored but worn clothes, <br>looking hungry and cold, asking for alms while standing on <br>their heads, juggling, or performing other little tricks.<br>Descriptor: A maze of old houses with faded walls. Weary <br>and hostile faces watch those who pass, while the poor and <br>hungry ask for alms along the streets.<br>Information: Depending on their ability to ask questions <br>and examine clues, Hunters may discover some or all of the <br>following information: <br> ◆ The general sentiment of the population with regard <br>to the recent murders, rumor of which has spread, is of <br>ill-concealed approval. The blank, unconcerned gazes <br>of any commoners interviewed makes it clear they <br>think the nobles deserved it. <br> ◆ This is a good point of contact between the Hunters <br>and some artists of the Circus of the Azure Sun. See <br>the section Cibulka Tavern for available information. <br> ◆ If they visit Georg, the characters find him drunk in his <br>house, and very aggressive. If subdued or persuaded to <br>speak, Georg will say that Konstantin is at his wits’ end <br>as the project he is leading on behalf of the city is not <br>going well. <br> ◆ The attic where Josef Slezák lived (see page 169) <br>burned down two days earlier. By convincing a couple <br>of soldiers to grant them access, the Hunters will <br>discover that the writer seems to have bought a huge <br>amount of wood, with which he feverishly filled the <br>stove until it exploded. The embers set fire to the rest <br>of the attic, devouring the roof of the house and Josef <br>himself. <br> ◆ If the Hunters are looking for him, Černobog (see <br>page 172) is not at home, as he is now permanently <br>stationed at the Circus of the Azure Sun. By breaking <br>in, however, they will be able to access his rooms. <br>There, the boy still keeps his mother’s sewing tools <br>and the notebook where she noted expenses and <br>orders, including that for Danek Brzobohatý (one of <br>the victims, details on page 168). On the front of the <br>notebook, there is the name of the woman: Hedvika <br>Potměšil.<br>Georg Slanina the Helper <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I <br>do, I become a beast. <br>Agenda: Supporting my daughter, who now has to sell <br>matches on the street / Understanding why Konstantin fired <br>me.</p><p>168<br>Cibulka Tavern<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Cibulka’s entrance is <br>blackened by dirt, soot, and the effects of bad weather. You <br>cross a stone arch and, pushing a heavy wooden door, you find <br>yourself in a tavern built under sturdy red brick arches, with <br>solid wood tables and stools. Despite the slightly suffocating <br>atmosphere caused by the smoke from the kitchens and the <br>faint light from the torches, the climate seems jovial. The <br>smell of meat and beer mixes with the sweat of the patrons <br>and the smell of urine in the corners. Cibulka is a place <br>where workers and merchants mix, without paying too much <br>attention to the social class. You make your way through the <br>noise, looking for valuable information.      <br>Descriptor: A dark tavern, built under massive, red brick <br>arches. The smell of meat and beer mixes with the smell of <br>sweat and urine.<br>Information: Depending on their ability to ask questions <br>and examine clues, Hunters may discover some or all of the <br>following information:<br> ◆ Several patrons can confirm that on the evening of the <br>intrusion Konstantin was in Cibulka until late. This is <br>rare, as he usually leaves the place in the late afternoon <br>to devote himself to his lab work during the night. <br> ◆ At a table, you can find several members of the Circus <br>of the Azure Sun, which had been put up in a field <br>near the walls of Prague. They seem disconsolate and <br>complain about the lack of work and prospects, even if <br>they continue to order food and drinks. If questioned, <br>they will reveal that the circus was purchased roughly a <br>week earlier with a single ruby. The owner of the Circus <br>of the Azure Sun sold everything, tents, and animals, <br>without thinking twice. Most of the performers were <br>fired shortly after by the new owner, a strange boy <br>named Černobog Potměšil. <br> ◆ Some claim to have seen Konstantin and Bartoloměj <br>engaged in a heated discussion at one of the tables a <br>few nights ago. <br>The Czernin Family Palace<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: As you climb the stairs that <br>line the large fountain in front of the baroque palace of the <br>Czernin, you can only wonder how many rooms it contains <br>beneath its massive roof. “Here you can see the damage from <br>cannonfire during the siege, ” says a laconic servant as he <br>guides you through the majestic halls that lead to the room <br>where Danek’s body was found. When you arrive, Beáta <br>welcomes you, and apologizes for the absence of her husband, <br>who is apparently “indisposed. ” The room has not been <br>touched: on the canopy bed lies the rotting corpse of Danek <br>Brzobohatý, conspicuously lacking an arm. The man’s body <br>has cuts and abrasions all over his torso. He is dressed in an <br>elegant woman’s dress, now completely ruined.    <br>Descriptor: A large castle in the Baroque style, which still <br>bears the marks of the siege of Prague.<br>Information: Depending on their ability to ask questions <br>and examine clues, Hunters may discover some or all of the <br>following information:<br> ◆ Beáta admits that the dress was a gift for her which, <br>apparently, Danek had ordered a few weeks earlier. She <br>would have worn it to the upcoming ball organized by <br>the regent at Prague Castle. <br> ◆ On the dress, if examined carefully, the initials H.P . <br>(Hedvika Potměšil, mother of Černobog) can be found.</p><p>169<br>Beáta doesn’t know exactly how Danek got his dress, but <br>she suggests he probably used a common seamstress, <br>since in her opinion the dress is not even that beautiful. <br> ◆ If the body is examined carefully, it will be clear that the <br>cuts and abrasions were caused by a whip, while the arm <br>was removed with a hacksaw. With the right knowledge, <br>it will be possible to discover that the whip is similar to <br>those used to tame animals, while the hacksaw is of high <br>quality, as might be in the possession of certain men of <br>science. <br>The Theater<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You’re led inside the impressive <br>theater that stands out in front of the waters of the Vltava <br>river. A warm light is reflected on the golden mezzanines, and <br>beautiful red drapes lend the auditorium an extraordinary <br>elegance. This place is only for those who can afford it. Although <br>the murder happened several hours ago, nothing has been <br>touched while awaiting the Order’s investigation. The body of <br>the theater director Gabriel Černý is on Cleopatra’s throne, <br>missing a leg. The puddle of now-dried blood has stained the <br>stage. Bartoloměj looks at it with concern and declares: “We will <br>get back on our feet, and we will bring the audience back to the <br>theater even after this horrible tragedy. ”   <br>Descriptor: A large theater richly furnished, reserved only for <br>the wealthiest in Prague.<br>Information: Depending on their ability <br>to ask questions and examine clues, <br>Hunters may discover some or all of the <br>following information: <br> ◆ The corpse is missing a leg, which <br>has been severed cleanly, but <br>the man appears to have died of <br>strangulation. An analysis might <br>suggest that a large reptile, such as <br>a Boa constrictor, was used. Such <br>an animal is incredibly exotic in <br>Prague (it comes, in fact, from the <br>Circus of the Azure Sun). <br> ◆ At the time of the murder, all <br>the staff, including the actors, had <br>returned home. Since the script had <br>arrived late, Gabriel was finalizing the <br>last details, something he often did.<br> ◆ Bartoloměj had a deep disagreement with <br>the director, especially about the opening show: <br>a reinterpretation of Anthony and Cleopatra by <br>Shakespeare, which Gabriel Černý had commissioned <br>from “a hack of a writer” named Josef Slezák. Bartoloměj <br>had repeatedly advocated instead for a focus “on the <br>masterpieces of various Bohemian artists. ”<br> ◆ Some janitors say that Konstantin and Bartoloměj have <br>met a couple of times lately to go drinking together, in a <br>place called Cibulka. <br> ◆ To be revealed only after the visit to the alchemical <br>laboratory and after some pressuring: on the night of the <br>murder, Bartoloměj agreed to leave a side entrance to <br>the theater open, at Konstantin’s request. The alchemist <br>argued that he could “resolve the problem. ” Unless the <br>Hunters have Konstantin with them, the alchemist is <br>already hiding at the Circus of the Azure Sun.</p><p>170<br>Bartolomej Novotný the Assistant <br>Director of the Theater<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the young and ambitious assistant of <br>Gabriel Černý. Our differences were known. <br>Agenda: Make sure I am not blamed for the murder / <br>Make sure it doesn’t turn out that I facilitated the murder. <br>The Circus of the Azure Sun<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Just outside the walls of <br>Prague, a battered blue and white tent stands in a muddy <br>field. Some smaller tents are surrounded by wooden wagons, <br>while a secondary tent connected to the larger one acts as <br>a shelter from the weather for animals. There is a strange <br>silence, as if the field had been abandoned, except for a <br>subdued metallic sound coming from the animal tent.<br>Descriptor: A dilapidated tent in the middle of a muddy <br>field. Wooden carriages and abandoned animal cages.<br>The camp is not actually abandoned, and at several hours <br>of the day it’s possible to see a young boy hanging around <br>the tents (Černobog). Konstantin spends every free <br>moment in the animal tent, where he is assembling the <br>Prince, while the main tent is mostly empty, except for the <br>presence of a huge nest made up of brushes and mud built <br>a few meters from the ground, and accessible only through <br>the stairs or the ropes of the acrobats. <br>Information: Entering the Circus of the Azure Sun <br>without being seen by Černobog is difficult but, once <br>inside, Hunters can access some or all of the following <br>information:<br> ◆ There is a large basin containing human remains, <br>still wearing some uniforms of the Circus of the <br>Azure Sun. These are the artists who did not leave the <br>circus after the acquisition of Černobog, now simple <br>spare parts for the Prince. It will be possible to find a <br>hacksaw nearby. <br> ◆ On a desk you can find an invitation to the dance at <br>Prague Castle, under the name Konstantin Svoboda. <br>On another sheet there seems to be a rudimentary <br>map of the city, with a path traced (the one Konstantin <br>plans to use to get the Prince to the Castle). <br> ◆ The nest, suspended in the center of the tent, is made <br>up of mud and branches and is extremely similar to <br>that of a swallow. It’s big enough to accommodate a <br>human being. This is where Alexandr rests when he’s <br>not out murdering someone. <br> ◆ Approaching the circus at night, the Hunters will be <br>able to see strange lights coming from the animal tent: <br>Konstantin is in fact finalizing the preparations before <br>activating the Prince.<br>Refer to the Events section of the Scenario to better manage <br>the situation. <br>^</p><p>171<br>The Prince<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC <br>(6 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a Golem of blood <br>and flesh. There is only hatred in my <br>broken heart. <br>Agenda: Killing and tearing apart the ungrateful <br>people of Prague / I prefer to take my revenge on the <br>rich and powerful above all others. <br>Gift – Broken Heart:  Once per Scene, the Prince can <br>emit a freezing scream of pain that affects all living beings <br>in the area, causing 1 Penalty to any action against him. <br>Gift – Tornado of Blades:  The Prince’s body is <br>composed of arms, legs, and heads held together by a <br>metal structure. Any limb that can hold a blade <br>does. The Prince can start spinning, hitting <br>each opponent on his way in a single <br>attack, inflicting 1 Wound on anyone <br>who fails a Defense Check.</p><p>172<br>Aleksandr Pták<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am divided between who I was before and <br>the spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to <br>kill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.<br>Swallow’s Agenda: Finding an ally in the people I helped <br>in my previous life / Restoring the Prince, my only true love / <br>Avenging wrongs suffered. <br>Alexandr’s Agenda: Finding peace and freeing myself <br>from the spirit that possesses me. <br>Gift – Swallow’s Flight:  Aleksandr can easily climb <br>anywhere and perform inhuman leaps. As he does, his OL <br>increases by 1. If he hits someone plunging down from <br>above, he can automatically escape the enemy’s threat range <br>with a long jump. <br>Gift – What is Yours is Mine:  As an additional action, <br>Aleksandr can steal any object in the hands of another <br>character with extreme ease. A Hunter can avoid the theft  <br>by succeeding in a Defense Check.          <br> <br>Cernobog Potmešil The Child<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: The rubies I received allowed me to recover <br>from the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I <br>am now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger <br>and resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of <br>the poor people of Prague. <br>Agenda: Avenge my struggling mother / Make sure the rich <br>pay for their crimes.<br>Gift - The Ruby of Hate:  Černobog uses one of the two <br>rubies he obtained from the Swallow as bait to achieve <br>his goals. When he distracts someone with the ruby, he <br>prevents the use of a Gift for the duration of the Scene. If <br>the ruby is crushed, Černobog suffers 1 Wound.<br>Prague Castle<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: On the evening of the party, <br>you are greeted in the majestic ballroom of Prague Castle. <br>A cascade of crystal chandeliers illuminates white arches <br>finished with gold, while large mirrors magnify the already <br>remarkable size of the room, full of people dressed elegantly. <br>You hear your name announced aloud, and everyone seems <br>intrigued by your presence. Ostromir introduces you to the <br>various families of the city, but despite the superficially happy <br>atmosphere, the tension is palpable. <br>Descriptor: The great and magnificent Prague Castle.<br>When the ball is at its busiest, a wall will be violently <br>destroyed by a large creature of flesh and metal crashing <br>^^</p><p>173<br>in: the Prince. Behind him will follow Konstantin, drunk <br>with power, cursing Ostromir and those who lacked faith in <br>him. Konstantin will try to control the Prince, as much as <br>possible, directing the creature first towards Ostromir and <br>then against the others. <br>Refer to the Events of the Scenario for other potential <br>situations at Prague Castle. <br>In the event that all threats have already been eradicated, <br>you can use the dance as an epilogue, changing the vibe: <br>the aristocracy can go back to sleeping peacefully, even if <br>the ordinary people of Prague see this return to normality <br>as an additional sign of contempt that sooner or later will <br>result in open rebellion.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario there are five Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>The second night since the beginning of the <br>investigation in Prague:  there is rumor of another <br>murder of a prominent citizen (the Captain of the soldiers, <br>known for harassing the population). The details are left to <br>the Storyteller, but this is a good time to have the Hunters <br>near the crime scene and stage a chase with Alexandr on <br>the rooftops of the city. <br>The dance in Prague Castle will be held the third <br>night after the arrival of the Hunters:  unless <br>Konstantin’s plan is stopped. The Hunters will be invited as <br>guests of honor by Ostromir himself.  <br>If Konstantin is discovered or killed:  Konstantin <br>will try to turn the Prince against the Hunters. Lower the <br>Prince’s OL by 1 if Alexandr’s only murders are those of <br>Danek and Gabriel. If Konstantin is killed before activating <br>the Prince, the Hunters will only have to worry about <br>Alexandr and Černobog. The ball at Prague Castle can also <br>be used as a trap to attract remaining threats. <br>In case the Prince is eradicated, but not the others: <br>Alexandr and Černobog will attempt a desperate move to <br>infiltrate Prague Castle during the ball to kill Ostromir and <br>every other possible aristocrat. Konstantin, if alive, will flee <br>the city knowing he has lost everything. <br>If the Hunters prowl around Prague without <br>concealing their identity:  the less affluent classes <br>will be generally hostile towards the Hunters, especially <br>since word has spread that they are working for the hated <br>Ostromir Malý. More than a few thugs will be happy to <br>block their way, accusing them of protecting the powerful. <br>Even some soldiers, knowing their Captain will protect <br>them from repercussions, could hinder the Hunters or turn <br>violent against the population in the area of the rookery.</p><p>1<br>2<br>3a<br>4<br>5<br>3b<br>174<br>The Scenario I Will Stay with You Always in Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  The call of <br>Ostromir<br>It’s the same one you find on page 164, but there’s only <br>Konstantin present. The other two cases are mentioned, <br>but Ostromir says that Beáta and Bartoloměj will only be <br>available the next day. <br>After the interview with Ostromir, Konstantin will lead the <br>Hunters to the alchemical laboratory (page 165).<br>End of Scene: It will be clear that vital clues are hidden in <br>the poor neighborhoods of Prague. Go to THE SECOND <br>SCENE - The rookery and Cibulka.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735099,"modifiedTime":1781513735099,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"BhrjIBN82XnvN9Rr","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Will Stay with You Always - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE – The rookery <br>and Cibulka<br>Suggest that Hunters go and ask some questions in the <br>rookery or tavern (page 167). They’ll find clues there.<br>End of Scene:  From here on, let the Hunters decide <br>whether to go first to Beáta THIRD SCENE OPTION A <br>– The Czernin family palace or Bartoloměj THIRD SCENE <br>OPTION B – The theater.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735099,"modifiedTime":1781513735099,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9YmHwqWWGVcEsYtM","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Will Stay with You Always - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>The Czernin family palace <br>The Scene takes place as described on page 168.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can collect further clues by <br>interrogating Bartoloměj THIRD SCENE OPTION B – The <br>theater, or go to FOURTH SCENE – The circus.</p><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  <br>The theater<br>The Scene takes place as described on page 169.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can collect additional clues by <br>interrogating Beáta THIRD SCENE OPTION A – The <br>Czernin family palace, or go to FOURTH SCENE – The <br>circus.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735099,"modifiedTime":1781513735099,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MlFydMZ2ekFxmzcx","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Will Stay with You Always - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE –  The circus<br>The Hunters will arrive at the circus during the night. They <br>will see the lights in the animal tent, and they will encounter <br>Černobog, Konstantin, and the Prince. Aleksandr isn’t <br>there, but he still poses a threat.<br> <br>End of Scene: The Hunters are invited to the ball, go to <br>the FIFTH SCENE – Prague Castle.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735099,"modifiedTime":1781513735099,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4DSp7JL6xpZCbvqL","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Will Stay with You Always - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE –  Prague Castle<br>At this point the only threat left is Aleksandr, who in a last <br>desperate attempt will break into a window with the sole <br>aim of killing Ostromir.<br>End of Scene: the final clash will be against Aleksandr.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735099,"modifiedTime":1781513735099,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","collection":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","pages":"163-175"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735099,"modifiedTime":1781513735099,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Req2k0aFcgllOHrw","name":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","pages":[{"_id":"wilm0YALFrAWZ2RO","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> The Broken Ones</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 151-162.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-p151-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732623,"modifiedTime":1781513732623,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qy25A2INeAxYDfWd","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - Setup</h2><p>150<br>Once upon a time…<br>Vigo, a Galician port city. The Hunters were <br>summoned by the Countess of Vigo herself to <br>investigate two dangerous assassins with very <br>particular methods. Several mutilated bodies <br>have been found in recent weeks: three handsome <br>young girls, whose faces were removed by the two <br>murderers. An old spinner from the port saw two <br>cloaked figures wandering through the alleys of <br>the lower city, and that is why the Countess firmly <br>believes that this is the work of a pair of murderers <br>and not a single individual. It is not the first time <br>that something like this has happened. Ten years <br>ago, similar murders had disturbed the city, never <br>to be solved. The murders included ritualistic <br>elements using blood and flesh that brought to <br>mind the blackest of magic. The Countess fears <br>that, whatever hand held the knife, something dark <br>has come to hunt the people of Vigo. A ceremony <br>commemorating the ten-year anniversary of the <br>Count and the Countess is to be held soon, and the <br>shadow of the murders darkens what should be a <br>day of celebration for the whole city.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Cinderella (Charles Perrault)<br>In your Eyes, with <br>your Feet<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Murder / Torture / Mutilation</p><p>151<br>The story that led us here…<br>Ten years ago, Maria Di Bello, a wealthy widow who <br>had always been faithful to the King of Spain, lived in Vigo <br>with her three daughters. The elder two were the fruit of her <br>relationship with her beloved husband, while the youngest <br>was the unfortunate result of a one-night stand with a ship <br>captain. Maria had always loved everyone the same way: <br>Francisca the elder, Marta the middle daughter, and Cinder <br>the youngest. Cinder had been named for the strange gray <br>hair she had inherited from her father, strikingly contrasting <br>the intense blond hair of her mother and sisters. When the <br>current Count Azul of Vigo reached marrying age, Maria <br>offered all her daughters. Cinder was immediately rejected <br>due to her hair, described as “horrible” by the noble Azul. <br>Resentful and envious, Cinder turned to the Kind Mother, a <br>powerful witch residing in the port of Vigo who had hidden <br>her identity behind the curious name. With the Mother’s <br>help, Cinder committed several murders, removing skin <br>and hair from the victims and reshaping her body to look <br>exactly as Count Azul desired. Her mother and sisters <br>noticed the change, and Cinder was forced to silence them. <br>With her death near at hand, Maria appealed to what little <br>humanity she knew her daughter still had, asking her to at <br>least spare her sisters. Cinder agreed, but to ensure their <br>silence she maimed them both, digging out an eye and <br>cutting off one of their feet. One-eyed and lame, the two <br>sisters fled the city in hopes of a new life. <br>But fate was not kind to Francisca and Marta and, after <br>ten years as beggars and outcasts, they returned to Vigo. <br>Fueled by resentment and transformed by hate for their <br>cruel sister, the two have sworn revenge. In this, they are <br>supported by the now elderly Kind Mother, whose tongue <br>Cinder cut out after she asked the new Countess for one too <br>many favors. The ambition and ruthless cruelty of Cinder <br>has therefore forged a strange alliance, formed by all the <br>women she has wounded along the bloody road to a life of <br>luxury at the court of Vigo.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Cinder presents herself to the Hunters under the false <br>name of Princesca, the identity she used to seduce Azul. <br>The woman has many powers, such as enslaving animals <br>or disguising her appearance, as she has learned the art of <br>magic from the Kind Mother. The last remaining piece of <br>evidence that could link Cinder to her crimes is a pair of <br>glass slippers that the Kind Mother had created for her ten <br>years earlier. Clicking the heels of the magical slippers can <br>confuse or bewitch people. They were used to commit the <br>murders ten years ago, as Cinder bewitched her victims <br>so she could dissect them alive without interference. The <br>shoes fit Cinder’s feet perfectly, proving her involvement. In <br>addition, every night at midnight, Princesca returns to her <br>original appearance for a few minutes, revealing her true <br>identity before the magic recovers.<br>Francisca and Marta each wear a glass slipper and have <br>staged a return of the killer for two reasons: to put Cinder <br>under pressure, and to attract the attention of the Hunters <br>of the Order so that they shed light on the wicked actions <br>of their sister. The objective of the two is to be caught by the <br>Order and then try to bring the Hunters to their side.<br>Meanwhile, the Kind Mother plots her revenge. The old</p><p>1<br>152<br>witch is helping Francisca and Marta only to destabilize <br>Cinder. Once the Hunters begin closing in on Cinder, the <br>Kind Mother will ask the Countess to use magic to return <br>her tongue, promising to deal with the Hunters in return. <br>However, having regained speech, and consequently the <br>ability to perform magic, the Kind Mother will instead be <br>able to take revenge on that wretched girl who, ten years <br>earlier, trampled on everyone for her own gain.<br>Nota: In this Scenario, two NPCs have a double identity.<br>Cinder poses as Princesca, the Countess of Vigo. The <br>Kind Mother poses as the Old Port spinner. <br>Keep in mind that either name may be used without <br>explanation when discussing these characters.</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732624,"modifiedTime":1781513732624,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wxCNnroDyNEZVL8p","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You are led by a servant to <br>the great reception hall of the noble Vigo palace. The rich decor <br>and the large number of servants at work suggest that Count <br>Azul of Vigo is among the richest nobles in all of Galicia. <br>You are greeted by the Count himself, a handsome man in <br>his forties, and his wife Princesca. According to rumors still <br>circulating, she is a girl of humble origins picked from among <br>many candidates for her incredible beauty.<br>Place: The magnificent palace of Count Azul of Vigo.<br>Time: It is a hot summer morning.<br>Initial Situation: After a quick presentation by Count <br>Azul, Princesca will take the floor. The Countess will <br>explain what happened (the discovery of three corpses) and <br>how they were killed, which sadly recalls the events that <br>transpired ten years ago. From the interview, Hunters can <br>obtain the following information:<br> ◆ Ten years earlier, a murderer terrorized Vigo by killing <br>six young girls and removing parts of their skin and <br>hair. All the victims had in common were their blond <br>hair and their beauty.<br> ◆ The killer’s actions culminated in the massacre of an <br>entire family. Maria, Francisca, Marta, and Cinder Di <br>Bello were all killed the same night. This was the last <br>act of the killer before he disappeared forever. Note <br>that the other two victims were commoners killed <br>by Cinder so she could steal their beauty. They are <br>unrelated to the Di Bello family, and not important to <br>the current investigation. <br> ◆ In the last week, the bodies of three prostitutes who <br>frequented the port were found. All were known for <br>their beauty and a healthy head of blonde hair. Each of <br>them had the skin from their faces removed.<br> ◆ An old spinner who lives near the harbor is the only <br>witness. She told the guards of two black-clothed <br>figures who lured one of the victims into the shadows. <br>The girl followed the figures as if hypnotized, as if <br>sorceries and dark arts were involved.<br> ◆ As lord and lady of Vigo, Princesca and Azul instruct <br>the Hunters to unravel the mystery and thus put an end <br>to the murderer’s ten-year slaughter.<br> ◆ In a day, it will be the wedding anniversary of Azul and <br>Princesca and to celebrate the occasion there will be <br>a party in the summer palace located just outside the</p><p>153<br>city. The only obvious concern of the Count is <br>not to appear weak in front of his noble guests. <br>During the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters <br>that it is Princesca who holds the reins of the city, <br>and that her husband Azul is only a rich brat with <br>little concern for the sufferings of his subjects. It <br>will also be apparent that Princesca is nervous when <br>speaking to the Hunters. If asked about it, she will <br>deflect by reminding them of her (overly vague) <br>humble beginnings and highlighting how lucky she <br>was to marry the Count.<br>After the interview, Princesca will reveal to the <br>Hunters where to find the old spinner and the last <br>corpse. They’re both in the port area. <br>The Palace of Count Azul <br>of Vigo<br>Descriptor: A sumptuous noble palace in the city <br>center.<br>The Count Azul of Vigo<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a rich and bored nobleman who <br>cares only about social position. <br>Agenda: To waste time between parties and <br>pleasures, leaving the burden of leadership to my wife <br>Princesca.<br>Cinder Known to all as <br>Princesca of Vigo<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC  <br>(3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am Cinder and, thanks to <br>magic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind <br>Princesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind <br>Mother, I control the entire city. I am cold and <br>determined and I won’t let anyone stand in <br>my way. <br>Agenda: Gain wealth and power by <br>manipulating my stupid husband / Solving <br>the mystery of the new killer who behaves <br>exactly as I did ten years ago. <br>Gift – Kind Magic:  Cinder is able <br>to use the magic that the Kind Moth-<br>er taught her. As an action, Cinder <br>can cast one of the following spells.  <br>1. Animal Servants:  A group of <br>animals (up to 6 subjects) blindly <br>obeys the will of Cinder, even per -<br>forming suicidal actions. Cinder <br>has used this power many times <br>on a pair of doves until they <br>have been completely enslaved <br>(see The Doves on page 154);  <br>2. Transmutation:  An ob -<br>ject or a portion of the envi-<br>ronment mutates to be trans-<br>formed into something else. <br>The mutation lasts through-</p><p>154<br>out the Scene and cannot affect living beings; 3. Wish: A <br>subject (other than the one casting the spell) can express a <br>wish and it will come true. The Storyteller will decide the <br>nearest mechanical effect to accomplish the wish, whether <br>it is a new Descriptor, to heal one or more Wounds, or to <br>obtain a Gift. The effect of Wish cannot bring the dead back <br>to life, it only affects the subject who expresses it and lasts <br>until midnight.<br>Gift – Beauty Wish:  Thanks to the power of magic, <br>Cinder can assume any appearance she wants. The effect <br>lasts until midnight and usually Cinder uses it to maintain <br>the appearance of Princesca.  <br>The Doves<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC  <br>(1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are two doves enslaved by the power of <br>Cinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we <br>defend our mistress from all danger. <br>Gift – Go for the Eyes:  The Doves are skilled at hitting <br>the enemies’ weak spots. When a Dove manages to inflict a <br>Wound, it inflicts 1 additional Wound. In case of a positive <br>Outcome in a Defense Check, once per Scene, the Dove’s <br>attack will still inflict 1 Wound. This Gift cannot be used <br>more than once against the same target <br>during the Scenario.<br>The Port of Vigo<br>Descriptor: The great city’s port where ships from all over <br>the world are docked. The alleys in front of the port are a <br>crossroads of taverns, shops, and leisure houses. Even in the <br>middle of the night, there’s always life in the harbor. <br>Information: The Old Spinner resides in a small house <br>in the eastern part of the pier, while the last corpse was <br>found in the western area.<br>East of the pier:  The Hunters will be able to meet the <br>Kind Mother, who will present herself as an old silent <br>seamstress. Cinder knows that the spinner is the Kind <br>Mother, but gives no sign that she knows. The old witch <br>will communicate with the Hunters with some difficulty <br>and give them a brooch she found near the alley where <br>she saw the two cloaked silhouettes pass. The brooch bears <br>the coat of arms of the Di Bello family: the Kind Mother <br>herself will give directions to the Di Bello house, located in <br>the upper quarters of the city. The old witch will not follow <br>the Hunters, as she does not want to be seen by Francisca <br>and Marta.<br>West of the pier:  The Hunters will find Eduardo and <br>Felipe, two guards at the service of the Count of Vigo, <br>guarding the crime scene. The body of the young prostitute <br>(known as Estella) was moved to the icebox of an old fish <br>warehouse nearby.<br> ◆ The two guards will tell the Hunters that no one has <br>claimed her body. She is most likely one of the many <br>poor people just trying to get by. <br> ◆ Examining Estella’s body will confirm the removal <br>of all facial skin, performed with insane care. A very</p><p>155<br>precious ring was inserted in the young woman’s right <br>eye orbit. The ring has the coat of arms of the Countess <br>of Vigo engraved on it. The object was placed there by <br>Francisca and Marta to draw attention to Cinder. <br>The Kind Mother Known to all <br>as the Old Spinner<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am an old and powerful witch whose tongue <br>Cinder cut out. I can no longer use my magic, but I still have <br>potions and magic items to use for my purposes.<br>Agenda: Put Cinder under pressure so she asks for my help, <br>make her use Wish to give me back my tongue, and then use <br>my magic to take revenge on her. <br>Gift – Kind Magic:  As an action, the Kind Mother can <br>cast one of the following spells. 1. Animal Servants: A <br>group of animals (up to 6 subjects) blindly obeys the will <br>of the Kind Mother and even performs suicidal actions; <br>2. Transmutation:  An object or a portion of the <br>environment mutates to be transformed into something <br>else. The mutation lasts throughout the Scene and cannot <br>affect living beings; 3. Wish: A subject (other than the <br>one casting the spell) can and will express a wish. The <br>Storyteller will decide the nearest mechanical effect to <br>accomplish the wish, whether it is a new Descriptor, to heal <br>one or more Wounds, or to obtain a Gift. The effect of Wish <br>cannot bring the dead back to life, it only affects the subject <br>who expresses it and lasts until midnight. Note: The Kind <br>Mother cannot use this Gift unless she first finds a way to <br>heal her severed tongue.<br>Gift – Witch’s Treasures:  The Kind Mother possesses <br>a large number of magical objects and potions, which she <br>can use or give to her allies. Once per Scenario, she can <br>make use of each of these effects. 1. Potion: If ingested, <br>a potion bestows a Descriptor that provides an incredible <br>ability, such as flying or being invisible for the duration <br>of the Scene. No potion can grow her tongue back. 2. <br>Heirloom: The Kind Mother can get a hold of a Treasure <br>of the Order (page 5) that has not already been found <br>and is not in the possession of the Hunters.<br>Eduardo and Felipe<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are two guards who are content to leave <br>thinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as <br>little as possible.    <br>The Di Bello Family <br>House<br>Descriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois <br>districts of Vigo.<br>Information: Francisca and Marta live in the house <br>their mother abandoned. The two sisters traveled around <br>the world for a long time, but it was in mystical Prague <br>they underwent the strange rite that sewed their bodies <br>together. Now, the two women act as one creature, each <br>wearing on her foot one of the glass slippers that the Kind <br>Mother gave them. Francisca and Marta will be hostile to <br>the Hunters until they discover their identity. At that point,</p><p>156<br>the sisters will fall at their feet, begging them to expose <br>Cinder, who has escaped the consequences of her crimes <br>for ten years, hiding under the false identity of Princesca.<br> ◆ The two sisters are willing to do anything to get revenge <br>on Cinder, including going to prison or even giving up <br>their lives.<br> ◆ They will reveal to the Hunters that Cinder uses magic <br>to alter her appearance. Ten years earlier their mother <br>Maria had discovered the deception when she surprised <br>Cinder at the stroke of midnight, the moment each day <br>when she must recast her transfiguration spell.<br>Francisca and Marta the Vengeful <br>Sisters<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: We are two poor sisters sewn together in one <br>body. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate <br>effortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger. <br>Agenda: Discredit Princesca and reveal to everyone that <br>she is Cinder, our despised sister.<br>Gift – The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers:  Thanks to <br>the magical slippers the Kind Mother gave them, at every <br>step Francisca and Marta can click the glass heels and create <br>a resonance that generates a state of confusion in subjects <br>within forty feet. When a Hunter acts under the influence <br>of the Slippers, they must perform a Defense Check against <br>OL Medium 5 or lose their action for the Exchange. This <br>effect is considered mental manipulation. Once per Scene, <br>the two sisters can click their heels and cause a vibration <br>that damages the minds of those within reach. All affected <br>subjects must pass a Defense Check against OL Hard 7 or <br>suffer 1 Wound. Activating the Slippers is considered a free <br>additional action for the sisters. <br>Gift – As One Body:  Francisca and Marta can act twice <br>during an Exchange, once for each sister.<br>Count Azul of Vigo’s <br>Summer Residence<br>Descriptor: A beautiful villa in the countryside of Galicia.<br>Information: The feast for the tenth wedding anniversary <br>of Azul and Princesca is being held in the villa. Noblemen <br>and wealthy bourgeois are among the guests at the reception, <br>while a large troupe of acrobats has the task of brightening <br>up the evening with songs, dances, and juggling. A skilled <br>animal tamer has been arranged at the explicit request of <br>Princesca, who will therefore always have animals (a tiger <br>and a bear) to control with magic if need be.<br> ◆ Talking to the guests during the reception, the Hunters <br>will discover that after ten years, many are still <br>wondering how a girl of humble origins could steal the <br>heart of Count Azul.<br> ◆ At the stroke of midnight, before the great final toast, <br>Princesca will fake being dizzy to get away for those <br>few minutes she needs to cast her transfiguration spell.</p><p>157<br>Akim the Tamer<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC <br>(2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a brave and skilled <br>tamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear <br>Berto are both dear to me, as they obey <br>my every command.<br>Agenda: Perform and amaze the <br>audience with my animals / Prevent <br>anyone from harming Tasha and <br>Berto, whom I consider as my children.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>If the Hunters keep Princesca informed of the <br>investigation: the clever woman will quickly understand <br>that someone is framing her and will send Eduardo and <br>Felipe to deal with the Kind Mother. If the Hunters don’t do <br>something, the old witch won’t escape her fate. <br>If the Hunters defeat Francisca and Marta: the two <br>sisters will tell them everything they know, imploring the <br>Hunters to help expose Cinder.<br>If the Hunters unmask Cinder:  The Countess will <br>use the power of her magic to escape and run to the Kind <br>Mother for her help. Once she regains her voice thanks to <br>Cinder’s use of Wish, the Kind Mother will assist Cinder <br>to eliminate the Hunters and then take her time making <br>Cinder pay. <br>If the Hunters understand who the Kind Mother <br>really is: The witch will offer her aid in exchange for her <br>life and will seek their help in regaining her voice. <br>If the Hunters seek the support of Azul:  The Count <br>will pretend to be a fool and will even avoid taking measures <br>against Cinder once she has been unmasked. The man is <br>so willfully ignorant that he will ban the Hunters from the <br>city in order to keep his wife where she is, managing all the <br>responsibilities so he can lead a life of laziness. <br>If the Hunters trap Cinder during the anniversary <br>party: The woman will use magic to take control of Tasha <br>and Berto, sending them against the Hunters. Akim will <br>hinder the Hunters if they try to harm his beloved animals. <br>Cinder will try to escape to the Kind Mother by taking <br>advantage of the chaos. <br>Tasha the Tiger<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor <br>NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a fast and <br>aggressive, though trained, tiger.<br>Berto the Bear<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC  <br>(3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a strong and massive trained <br>bear.</p><p>158<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the In your Eyes, <br>with your Feet Scenario and can be acquired once the conditions <br>are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario Gift and if they <br>acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the previous one.<br>Gift – Kind Blessing<br>Requirement: Show a sincere interest in solving the mysterious <br>murders in Vigo to the Kind Mother.<br>A powerful witch has blessed you with protection against magic <br>and sorcery. Receive 2 Additional Successes when you make a <br>Defense Check against a magic effect. The first time you inflict 1 <br>Wound on a target using magic, the blessing dissipates until the <br>next Interlude.<br>Note: The Storyteller can offer this Gift to the Hunter who has met <br>the requirements without revealing who the witch who casts the <br>blessing is. Simply, the Hunter will become aware that someone is <br>trying to help them.<br>Gift – The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers (Treasure of <br>the Order)<br>Requirement: Defeat Francisca and Marta.<br>Obtain the Treasure of the Order The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers, <br>see page 25 of the Treasury of the Order.</p><p>1<br>2a 2b<br>159<br>The Scenario Through your <br>Eyes, with your Feet in <br>Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  The Regents of <br>Vigo<br>It’s the same one you find on page 152. The Hunters will <br>talk to Azul and Princesca.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters can decide whether to <br>interrogate the Old Spinner, go to SECOND SCENE <br>OPTION A – The Old Spinner. Or examine the body of the <br>last victim, go to SECOND SCENE OPTION B – The crime <br>scene.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732624,"modifiedTime":1781513732624,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jJuzzgniHRhbsPj9","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION A <br>– The Old Spinner<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: The port of Vigo is very busy <br>and represents the heart of the city. Its importance can be seen <br>clearly in the constant flow of goods and the ships crowded at <br>the docks. Following the directions given by Princesca, you <br>come to a small house in one of the alleys right next to a large <br>fish market, each fisherman setting up his stall directly on his <br>docked boat. You find the door to the small open dwelling, <br>and when you enter you see the figure of an old lady sewing. <br>The woman opens her mouth as if to greet you, but no <br>sound emerges. It quickly becomes clear her tongue has been <br>removed, leaving only a stump behind in her mouth. <br>Place: A small house that the spinner also uses as a <br>tailoring workshop. <br>Time: It is late morning and the smell of fresh fish coming <br>from the fishermen’s ships tickles the nostrils. <br>Information: The Kind Mother will welcome the <br>Hunters, trying to make herself understood to the best of <br>her ability, and will give the same information presented <br>on page 155. <br>End of Scene: Having obtained the brooch and directions <br>to the house of the Di Bello family, the Hunters can go there <br>to investigate. Go to THIRD SCENE – The old house of the <br>Di Bello family. Or examine the body of the last victim, go <br>to SECOND SCENE OPTION B – The crime scene.<br>Note: For correct management of the clues, the Hunters <br>must go to an interview with the Old Spinner before the</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732624,"modifiedTime":1781513732624,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Zo1B4LXx7mUNY3Hc","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE – The old house of the Di Bello family.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732624,"modifiedTime":1781513732624,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jJuzzgniHRhbsPj9","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION B – <br>The crime scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The port of Vigo is very <br>busy and represents the heart of the city. Its importance can <br>be seen clearly in the constant flow of goods and the ships <br>crowded at the docks. Following the instructions given by <br>Princesca, you arrive at an old warehouse that is now being <br>used as a morgue. Two men who look quite drowsy guard the <br>front door.<br>Place: An old warehouse in the western part of the port. <br>Time: It is late morning. A large ship from the Americas is <br>docking at the port.</p><p>3<br>160<br>Information: Eduardo and Felipe will be well disposed <br>towards the Hunters, letting them in to examine the body <br>of the victim. They can discover the information on page <br>155. <br>End of Scene: With all the doubts that the ring can put in <br>the minds of the Hunters, there are still some fundamental <br>clues missing. They can go and talk to the Old Spinner. Go <br>to SECOND SCENE OPTION A – The Old Spinner. Or, if <br>they’ve been there already, they can head to the THIRD <br>SCENE – The old house of the Di Bello family.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732624,"modifiedTime":1781513732624,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Zo1B4LXx7mUNY3Hc","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE –  The old house <br>of the Di Bello family<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The house of the Di <br>Bello family is an elegantly imposing villa that, despite its <br>abandonment, stands out among the houses of the upper <br>districts of Vigo. Sun-bleached curtains in the second-floor <br>windows have been disturbed, perhaps by new occupants of <br>the long-abandoned home.<br>Place: The grand, abandoned house of the Di Bello family.<br>Time: It is just past noon.<br>Information: Francisca and Marta are in the house. As <br>soon as the Hunters enter, they will be attacked by the sisters. <br>Once defeated, the two women will reveal their identities <br>and the whole story of Cinder, asking for the Hunters’ help <br>in unmasking their sister. The two will suggest that the <br>Hunters confront Cinder during the wedding anniversary <br>party that will be held the following evening.<br> ◆ The two sisters will confess that they are using the <br>same methods and plan that Cinder used ten years <br>earlier. They will also say that they put the ring in the <br>victim’s eye (if the Hunters have found it) to guide the <br>investigation towards the Countess.<br> ◆ The two sisters will say they were helped by an old <br>witch who gave them the slippers. The woman left  <br>them the shoes without saying a word, so the sisters <br>could not see her face.<br>End of Scene:  It will now be clear to the Hunters that <br>the Countess hides a secret, go to the FOURTH SCENE – <br>Unmasking the Countess.</p><p>4<br>161</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732625,"modifiedTime":1781513732625,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"poJdKwFXYFnp5HDF","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE –  Unmasking the <br>Countess<br>This scene can develop in many ways and in many possible places, so <br>it’s presented below with different tips for managing your Scenario.<br>If the Hunters want to unmask Cinder: The best way will be to <br>catch her red-handed while casting the spell to alter her appearance <br>at midnight. If they wish to, the Hunters will be welcome to attend <br>the reception. Once unmasked, Cinder will stir up the beasts of <br>Akim against the Hunters, then try to flee to the Kind Mother <br>for help.<br>If the Hunters tell everything to Princesca: The Countess <br>will thank them, trying to dismiss them as soon as possible, and <br>then move her guards to arrest her sisters and the Kind Mother. <br>If the Hunters do nothing, the three women will disappear into <br>the dungeons of the castle never to be seen again.<br>If the Hunters attempt to expose the Kind Mother:  <br>The old witch will try to play on their pity to avoid being <br>handed over to the Order. The old woman’s primary goal  is <br>to regain her tongue thanks to Cinder’s magic. Once she has <br>done that, she will try to eliminate every potential witness, <br>Hunters included.<br>End of Scene:  However the Scene goes, once again the <br>fate of the unfortunate protagonists of this story will be in <br>the hands of the Hunters.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732625,"modifiedTime":1781513732625,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","collection":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","pages":"151-162"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732625,"modifiedTime":1781513732625,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VVrgslOKg1WL5E8j","name":"Hunger Island","pages":[{"_id":"2UZFtzmD86xPSaDM","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Hunger Island</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> The Broken Ones</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 93-108.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/hunger-island-p93-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714972,"modifiedTime":1781513714972,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jAv5HHl7OrDVyikq","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Hunger Island - Setup</h2><p>92<br>Once upon a time…<br>Strange news comes from far away Iceland: the <br>great volcano Laki has unleashed its full might <br>and has stricken down the poor inhabitants of <br>the small villages on the island, like a divine <br>punishment. Few have managed to escape the fury <br>of fire and ash, but one in particular, the humble <br>logger Heino, tells of strange events in his village <br>and of an ancient power that seems to have taken <br>possession of many young inhabitants. The first <br>rescue expedition was sent to the small village of <br>Hosn, but no news has reached Denmark for over <br>a month. Considering Heino’s delirious tales, the <br>crown has decided to turn directly to the Papacy <br>for help, hoping the Church can determine if the <br>Devil himself could be behind the terrible famine. <br>A small ship has set sail for Iceland, though the <br>island is still shrouded in the fumes of Laki’s fury. <br>Among the crew is a group of Hunters, handpicked <br>to unravel this mystery.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Hansel <br>and Gretel (Grimm Brothers)<br>Hunger Island<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Cannibalism / Catastrophe / Deprivation</p><p>93<br>The story that led us here…<br>A few months have passed since the eruption of <br>the volcano Laki, which has wiped out most of the livestock <br>and inhabitants of the island, throwing Iceland into the <br>greatest famine of its history. In the village of Hosn, the <br>residents have found a macabre way to stave off starvation. <br>They sacrifice and feed on the weakest among them. Heino, <br>a poor woodcutter, sensed that his beloved children Hanse <br>and Gréte would be the next victims. Rather than see them <br>served up as meat, Heino led them to the base of Laki, <br>where he hoped they would find a quicker and less painful <br>end. In the mists and fumes of the volcano, however, <br>the two young people did not find death, but an ancient <br>stone, fallen from the sky at the dawn of the world itself. <br>Corrupted by the power enclosed in it, Hanse and Gréte <br>have changed, becoming superhuman beings who need <br>fresh meat to constantly regenerate their bodies. Deciding <br>to spread their new ‘gifts’ , the two children returned to <br>Hosn. Brother and sister infected the other village children <br>with the stone’s power, putting power in new hands. Now <br>adults have become livestock for the children exposed to <br>the power of the stone. The new mutants call themselves <br>Maws, the name by which Hanse and Gréte baptized this <br>new breed of Icelandic people. In one case, however, Hanse <br>granted his sister’s Gréte request for mercy. The two Maws <br>escorted their father to the port of Vík í Mýrdal, putting <br>him on one of the last ships to leave for the continent.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Most of the island is under the control of the Maws, who <br>lack fresh food and now guard Vík í Mýrdal in the hope of <br>ambushing incoming ships. Berend, captain of the ship of <br>the previous expedition, and Althea, a traveling nun in the <br>service of the Order, are also hiding in Vík í Mýrdal, now <br>a ghost town. The Maws control the only two inhabited <br>places that escaped the fury of the volcano Laki: the port <br>of Vík í Mýrdal and the village of Hosn. They also guard <br>the volcano itself, where the stone is venerated as a deity. <br>The lack of food has made the Maws increasingly aggressive <br>and violent, and even Hanse and Gréte are beginning to <br>struggle to keep them in control. In Hosn, where the few <br>remaining humans are kept in a large cage waiting to be <br>slaughtered, Hanse must increasingly maintain order by <br>force, to prevent the most hungry Maws from massacring <br>the few survivors and consuming all the food stocks in <br>one night. In Vík í Mýrdal, Gréte leads a group of the most <br>faithful Maws, looking for a way to attract new boats to the <br>island.</p><p>1<br>94</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714973,"modifiedTime":1781513714973,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"99BSKLablvmbK9AW","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Hunger Island - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  After more than a week of <br>sailing, you finally catch a glimpse of the Icelandic coast and the <br>outlines of the port of Vík í Mýrdal. The smoking silhouette of the <br>great volcano stands out on the horizon like a hulking monster <br>looming over the entire island. With a few skillful maneuvers, <br>Captain Arne guides the ship into port, easily navigating the <br>thick blanket of fog and soot that seems to envelop everything. <br>The air is heavy and, around you, the world is a clouded, smoky <br>gray. You can feel a thrill of fear going up your back as you <br>contemplate the unnatural silence surrounding the port. No one <br>is present to welcome you and, at a closer look, the city seems <br>deserted.<br>Place: The port of Vík í Mýrdal, lost in fog.<br>Time: It is early afternoon, even though the fog that covers <br>the whole island means the light is dulled to the point of soft  <br>twilight.<br>Initial Situation: The ship is docked in the port and it is <br>immediately clear to everyone that the city is uninhabited. <br>The ship that brought the previous expedition is docked not <br>far away, looking abandoned as well. <br>Information: When interacting with Captain Arne, the <br>Hunters will learn that the entire crew is quite tense. The sailors <br>are skilled sea wolves, and for this reason deeply superstitious. <br>Only Arne, who comes from a military background, remains <br>cold and calculating at the spectacle of the ghost port. Arne <br>will guarantee the full support of his men to the Hunters: it <br>will be up to them to decide whether or not to make use of <br>the support. <br>Note: In this Scenario the Hunters will travel between Vík <br>í Mýrdal, the village of Hosn, and the volcano Laki. Each <br>journey takes 2 days on foot and must pass through The Mist <br>Roads (page 98).<br>Arne the Captain<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I once was a military man and I’ve earned the <br>crown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and <br>boast about my crew. <br>Agenda: Do my best to carry out the mission I was entrusted <br>with. However, I won’t put the people under my command at <br>risk.<br>Sailors<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We <br>are skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.<br>Agenda: Execute Arne’s orders and avoid in any way having to <br>face the supernatural.</p><p>95<br>The Port of Vík í <br>Mýrdal<br>Descriptor: The large port of a city <br>that was built to be a point of arrival <br>from the mainland. Ships and houses are <br>in a state of complete disuse.<br>Information: Walking around the <br>port and on the ship of the previous <br>expedition, the Hunters can obtain in <br>order the following information:<br> ◆ The city is indeed deserted. Crates <br>still hanging on hoists and torches <br>left untended, so that parts of the <br>docks are charred and burned, <br>suggest that the inhabitants have <br>abandoned what they were doing <br>when disaster struck.<br> ◆ Traces of blood and the remains of <br>devoured humans can be found in <br>the dark recesses of the harbor. It is <br>as if a pack of wild beasts assaulted the inhabitants to <br>drag them into darkness and devour them.<br> ◆ In the small harbor master’s office, the Hunters will <br>find on the front door a message written in blood: the <br>lighthouse is safe. The message is written in poor Latin, <br>with the clear intention of making it unreadable for the <br>natives of the island. It indicates the place where Althea <br>and Berend took refuge, and was written by the nun for <br>a possible group of Hunters. <br>For any information the Hunters receive, <br>you can decide to roll a die or choose <br>what happens:<br>1-2: A group of 8 Maws ambushes the <br>Hunters.<br>3-4: A group of 8 Maws led by Gréte <br>ambushes the Hunters. Gréte will <br>remain on the sidelines to lead the <br>attack and gather information about the <br>newcomers.<br>5-6: Berend watches the Hunters from <br>afar to discern who they are and why <br>they’ve come. He will eventually try to <br>approach them for help, but only when <br>it is safe from the Maws.<br>Gréte<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC  <br>(4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the incarnation of <br>the power of the great Maw. My body <br>regenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my <br>speed are unbelievable. <br>Agenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future <br>for the Maw’s offspring. Unlike my brother Hanse, I still have <br>a shred of humanity and I wouldn’t want to devour anyone <br>indiscriminately / I want to convince my friend Ina to become <br>a Maw.<br>Gift – Mutant Maw:  As long as they maintain their <br>original appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as <br>a common child. When they unleash their power, the body <br>shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a</p><p>96<br>long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a <br>higher OL category for every physical action they perform <br>involving speed, strength, or ferocity. A mutant perceives <br>the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, and <br>for this reason every attempt to hide from their sense of <br>smell receives 1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour <br>flesh (human or animal), they cannot stop until they have <br>finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw inflicts <br>1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound <br>they suffered.<br>Gift – First Maw:  As the firstborn among the Maws, <br>Gréte has learned to manipulate the power that she <br>harbors in her body. During a Scene, Gréte may self-inflict <br>1 Wound to benefit from one of the following effects:  <br>1. Superhuman Strength, if she inflicts 1 Wound with <br>an action and does not devour the target, Gréte can throw <br>it 15 feet away. The target will fall to the ground and suffer 1 <br>additional Wound if they impact an obstacle. Gréte can use <br>her strength to throw one enemy into another, in which case <br>the target can try to dodge the attack with a Defense Check. <br>2. Superhuman Speed , Gréte can make an incredible <br>leap of over 30 feet. She does not need any preparation, <br>and she can take another subject with her while moving. <br>3. Rebirth, Gréte falls into a state of apparent death to <br>regenerate in the next Scene. She wakes up completely <br>healed. Only a highly skilled doctor or someone using <br>magical means is able to discern Gréte is not truly dead.  <br>The Maws<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: We are a new people, children of the great <br>Maw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our <br>strength and speed are incredible. <br>Agenda: We obey Gréte and Hanse, they are the firstborns, <br>they know the right path / Satiate our infinite hunger, even at <br>the cost of disobeying the firstborns.<br>Gift – Mutant Maw:  As long as they maintain their <br>original appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as <br>a common child. When they unleash their power, the body <br>shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing <br>a long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a <br>higher OL category for every physical action they perform <br>involving speed, strength, or ferocity. A mutant perceives <br>the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, and <br>for this reason every attempt to hide from their sense of <br>smell receives 1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour <br>flesh (human or animal), they cannot stop until they have <br>finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw inflicts <br>1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound <br>they suffered.</p><p>97<br>Berend the Crazed Captain <br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the captain of the previous expedition <br>and the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by <br>masking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.<br>Agenda: Wait for someone to come from the mainland to <br>save me.<br>Gift – Stinking Survivor:  Berend managed to avoid <br>being devoured by the Maws, but what he saw happen <br>to his companions scarred his mind forever. The man <br>constantly covers himself with rotten fish because he has <br>discovered the stench conceals him from the Maws. <br>Berend will never be targeted by a Maw unless he <br>takes direct action against them. As long as he <br>is at the port of Vík í Mýrdal, Berend can move <br>with great skill through the alleys and take <br>any companions anywhere in the city without <br>attracting the attention of the Maws. Each <br>time he uses this ability, he rolls 1 die: on 5 <br>or 6, Berend convinces himself that he has <br>seen other survivors and makes noise in an <br>attempt to get their attention. It will be <br>clear to those that accompany him that <br>the whole situation is nothing <br>more than a figment <br>of the poor man’s <br>distressed mind.<br>Vík í Mýrdal’s Lighthouse<br>Descriptor: An old lighthouse in the oldest part of the port <br>of Vík í Mýrdal. Crates of fish have been broken open and <br>spilled around the lighthouse, their contents left to rot in the <br>sun. Now, the air reeks in a nauseating way.<br>Gift – Safe Haven from the Maws: The stacks of rotten <br>fish that Berend and Althea constantly throw at the foot of <br>the lighthouse keep the Maws away. The Maws lose all trace <br>of someone who takes refuge in the lighthouse. While near <br>the lighthouse, Maws reduce their Opposition Level by 1.<br>Information: Althea will have a great deal of information <br>for the Hunters. She has been trapped for a month now, and <br>has taken the opportunity to study the Maws in depth.<br> ◆ The Maws look like children mutated by something. <br>They are strong, fast, and seem to follow the smell of <br>human flesh.<br> ◆ Some desperate people fleeing from the village of Hosn <br>have told them of two “leaders” of the Maws, brother <br>and sister, who apparently are smarter and more <br>powerful than the others.<br> ◆ After overhearing Maws talking to each other, Althea <br>realized that the volcano is a sacred place for those <br>strange beings that humans must not enter.<br> ◆ Both the village and the volcano are two days’ walk <br>from Vík í Mýrdal, but in different directions.</p><p>98<br>Althea the Agent of the Order<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a nun in the service of the Order and, <br>despite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and <br>a fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because <br>it has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.<br>Agenda: Solve the mystery of the Maws and provide support <br>to the Hunters of the Order.<br>Gift – Agent of the Order: Althea is talented and trained to support the Hunters. Althea can spend her action to <br>support a Hunter’s action and give them 1 Additional <br>Success in any Check.<br>The Mist Roads<br>Descriptor: All the communication routes between Vík í <br>Mýrdal and the nearby villages are surrounded by a dense, <br>dark fog that does not allow you to see more than a few feet <br>ahead.<br>For each trip on the Mist Roads, you can choose or roll for <br>a Threat/encounter with an NPC.<br>1-2: A crevasse created by the eruption of Laki has <br>opened up, barring the way.<br>Threat – Crevasse in the Mist <br>Descriptor: A crevasse eighteen feet deep, hidden by the <br>dense mist.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Falling into the crevasse will cause 1 Wound. At the bottom, <br>you can find the body of a desperate runaway. As a cost for <br>a Defense Check Outcome, a Hunter may lose equipment <br>that will fall down into the mist.<br>3-4: The mist becomes even thicker, making it <br>impossible to even distinguish the road.<br>Threat – Mist Wall<br>Descriptor: A fog so dense that it is impossible to see <br>anything.<br>OL Hard 7<br>If they fail a Check to stay on the road, the Hunters will get <br>lost and end up in the wrong place.<br>5-6: A group of Maws. A group of 4 Maws who travel in <br>search of fresh meat.</p><p>99<br>The Village of Hosn<br>Descriptor: A small village lost in the hills. Many houses <br>have been burned down, and the stench of corpses hovers in <br>the air.<br>Information: The village is under Hanse’s control. In the <br>small central square, a rudimentary wooden cage was built <br>where the last six inhabitants of the village are trapped. <br>Every day, one inhabitant is taken out to be devoured, but <br>now there are more than twenty Maws and so little flesh is <br>not enough to satisfy their hunger. <br>By saving the inhabitants, the Hunters will be able to obtain <br>some information:<br> ◆ Ina is a little girl who refused to become a Maw. She is a <br>friend of Gréte, who explicitly asked her brother Hanse <br>to keep Ina last, in the hope that she will change her <br>mind and convert. Ina is aware of the friendship that <br>Gréte feels towards her and how this is a weak point <br>within the Maw.<br> ◆ Askell is a young hunter who killed a Maw when Hanse <br>and Gréte took control of the village. As punishment his <br>hands were devoured and now Askell is kept alive only <br>to see all his loved ones die one after the other. He hates <br>the Maws and killing them has become an obsession <br>for him. Askell knows a secret road that allows you to <br>reach the volcano, avoiding the complications of the <br>Mist Roads. <br> ◆ Alba is Askell’s mother. She is now utterly devastated, <br>after seeing her husband Helg eaten alive by the Maws <br>and her son reduced to impotence. Alba has a key to <br>the cellars of the town hall, a shelter from volcanic <br>eruptions where many supplies are stashed. <br> ◆ Enoch is one of the village elders. He was the first to <br>acknowledge the idea of eating the helpless to survive. <br>All the Maws hate him and would attack him without <br>a second thought, if only they had the chance. Hanse <br>keeps him alive, pondering the most convoluted <br>possible way to eliminate him when the time comes.<br> ◆ Erna is a young woman without children. She has <br>always hated living on the island and was only here to <br>follow her husband who has already been devoured <br>by the Maws. Erna has heard Hanse talking to other <br>Maws about a “stone that came from the sky” kept in <br>the volcano, which must be defended at all costs. <br> ◆ Hafnar is a plump businessman who is being fed with <br>the little food left in the village. Hanse’s intention is to <br>fatten up Hafnar to make him more delicious for his <br>Maws. Hafnar possesses a dose of a potent rat poison <br>that he has already used to kill two Maws in the first <br>few days. His intention is to sprinkle his body with <br>the poison on the day he is devoured, to take as many <br>Maws with him as possible.</p><p>100<br>Hanse<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor:  I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body <br>regenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable. <br>Agenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future for the Maw’s offspring. <br>Unlike my sister Gréte, I have no regard for humans and, now that I spared my <br>father to make my sister happy, I just want to protect the stone that came from <br>the sky.<br>Gift – Mutant Maw:  As long as they maintain their original appearance, a <br>mutant Maw appears in every way as a common child. When they unleash their <br>power, the body shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a <br>long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a higher OL category <br>for every physical action they perform involving speed, strength, or ferocity. <br>A mutant perceives the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, <br>and for this reason, every attempt to hide from their sense of smell receives <br>1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour flesh (human or animal), they <br>cannot stop until they have finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw <br>inflicts 1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound they suffered.<br>Gift – First Maw:  As the firstborn among the Maws, Hanse has learned <br>to manipulate the power that he harbors in his body. During a Scene, <br>Hanse may self-inflict 1 Wound to benefit from one of the following effects:  <br>1. Superhuman Strength , if he inflicts 1 Wound with an action and <br>does not devour the target, Hanse can throw it 15 feet away. The target <br>will fall to the ground and suffer 1 additional Wound if they impact an <br>obstacle. Hanse can use his strength to throw one enemy into another, in <br>which case the target can try to dodge the attack with a Defense Check.  <br>2. Superhuman Speed , Hanse can make an incredible leap of over 30 <br>feet. He does not need any preparation, and he can take another subject with <br>him while moving. 3. Power of the Stone that Came from the Sky , <br>Hanse can tap into the latent power in his body. Once per Scene, all human <br>subjects in his presence lose 2 Soma or alternatively can resist by taking 1 <br>Wound. Suffering the last Wound for this effect does not cause death, but a <br>loss of consciousness.</p><p>101<br>Laki the Volcano<br>Descriptor: A great volcano that dominates all of Iceland. <br>The rock walls have cracked due to the powerful eruptions, <br>creating a series of natural tunnels and galleries. <br>Information: The volcano hides the stone that came <br>from the sky among a maze of tunnels. After the first <br>eruptions, the stone has re-emerged, manifesting its power. <br>To protect the stone, Hanse has left all the Maws that have <br>had issues managing the mutations at the volcano. Those <br>abandoned wretches have grown into Crazed Maws, <br>brainless monsters who wander in search of food. It’s <br>possible for the Hunters to track the Crazed Maws to the <br>stone’s hiding place. Otherwise, the Hunters will face the <br>Threat Daedalus of Tunnels.<br>Threat – Daedalus of Tunnels<br>Descriptor: A series of natural tunnels that change shape <br>according to the tectonic shocks that hit the volcano.<br>OL Hard 7<br>Failing the Check means getting lost, meeting one or more <br>Crazed Maws, or ending up caught in a sudden lava flow, <br>which inflicts 1 Wound and the destruction of one or more <br>pieces of equipment.<br>Crazed Maws<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: A mad abomination whose form constantly <br>shifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour. <br>Agenda: Eat every living thing, except other Maws.<br>Gift – Mutant Abomination:  A Crazed Maw does not <br>feel any pain. For this reason the Wounds it suffers have <br>no narrative effect but are only a counter to understand <br>when the abomination will crumble into a thousand pieces. <br>Tentacles and arms are constantly born from the body of <br>a Crazed Maw, and as a result it can act 2 times during <br>an Exchange. With one of its actions, a Crazed Maw can <br>slam its huge mass to the ground to create a strong tremor. <br>All targets in the immediate vicinity must pass a Defense <br>Check to avoid falling to the ground.<br>Threat – The Stone that Came from <br>the Sky<br>Descriptor: An alien stone, the size of a fist, that thrums <br>with energy. <br>Gift – Alien Stone:  All the powers of the Maws derive <br>from the stone. With its destruction, the mutations will <br>deteriorate, causing the death of all mutants except Hanse <br>and Gréte. The stone has 6 Wounds and has no OL, because <br>it cannot interact directly or defend itself. For each Wound <br>suffered, a spark of the power comes out, affecting the one <br>who inflicted the blow. Whoever suffers this effect can <br>decide between losing 2 Soma or suffering 1 Wound. If the <br>stone is destroyed or stolen, Hanse will be able to unleash <br>all the latent power in him and, by joining with Gréte, give <br>life to the Great Maw.</p><p>102<br>Threat – The Great Maw<br>Descriptor: A colossal titan of flesh and tentacles born from <br>the union of the two first Maws. The creature acts to recover <br>the stone or avenge its destruction, at the cost of destroying the <br>entire island in the process.<br>OL Hard 7<br>Note: The Storyteller must immediately clarify that the <br>Great Maw is a monster so powerful that it cannot be faced <br>in combat. Its ever-growing mass instantly regenerates every <br>wound, and its colossal size is beyond the reach of any magic. <br>Rather than confronting the Great Maw, the Hunters must <br>curb its action as they rescue the survivors.<br>Here is a list of potential situations:<br> ◆ The stone can be used as bait to force the Great Maw to <br>follow it. Throwing it in the middle of the volcano will <br>cause the titan to follow it, burning to death in a lava pit.<br> ◆ One can still leverage Gréte’s consciousness and her <br>sympathy for Ina, making the Great Maw hesitate for a <br>few moments before Hanse regains control.<br> ◆ When a Defense Check against the Great Maw is failed, <br>in addition to suffering 1 Wound, the target will be <br>pushed away by over thirty feet, suffering 1 additional <br>Wound if it impacts something.<br> ◆ With the force of its roar alone, the Great Maw can hurl <br>a human to the ground.<br> ◆ With a tentacle, the Great Maw can “pick up” a house and <br>hurl it at someone.<br> ◆ Escaping the Great Maw is not easy and the survivors of <br>the village will be a burden for the Hunters.<br> ◆ The Great Maw cannot swim and will stop its chase once <br>the Hunters successfully take to the sea.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel free <br>to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunters.<br>If the Hunters dismantle the Maw packs in Vík í <br>Mýrdal: Gréte will approach the Hunters pretending to <br>be a survivor. The intention of the Maw is to study these <br>new enemies and provide useful information to her brother <br>Hanse.<br>If the Hunters send sailors alone to explore the port <br>of Vík í Mýrdal: in a short time, the poor unfortunate will <br>be attacked and overwhelmed by the Maws.<br>If Gréte understands that the Hunters are here to <br>save the inhabitants:  the Maw could reveal herself and <br>negotiate to save her friend Ina.<br>If the Hunters arrive in Hosn without worrying <br>about being seen: all the Maws will present themselves as <br>common children and ambush the Hunters when their guard <br>is down. <br>If the Hunters steal or destroy the stone that came <br>from the sky:  mad with rage, Hanse will join his sister <br>Gréte to fuse into the Great Maw.<br>If Gréte is cornered by the Hunters:  she will use her <br>gift to appear dead and, as soon as she wakes up, she will run <br>to join her brother.</p><p>103<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the Hunger <br>Island Scenario and can be acquired once the conditions are <br>met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario Gift and if they <br>acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the previous one.<br>Stinky<br>Requirement: Meet Berend and learn from him how to <br>mask your scent.<br>Y ou know how to make your scent unrecognizable and <br>confuse enemies and predators. Y ou can spend 1 Soma and <br>cover yourself with a rotting substance that will make you <br>smelly. An enemy who bases their actions on smell (like a <br>Maw) will never target you unless you act directly against <br>them. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success to all Defense Checks <br>you make to defend from an attack carried out by an enemy <br>sensitive to your aroma. Y ou receive 1 Penalty at all Checks <br>with ordinary people when your nauseating smell is a clear <br>obstacle. <br>The Stone that Came from the Sky<br>Requirement: Recover the stone that came from the sky <br>from the slopes of the volcano.<br>Y ou hold an alien stone with great powers, which you can <br>activate by suffering 1 Wound. When you do, choose from <br>one of the following effects. 1. Might: Y our strength triples <br>and you get 1 Additional Success to any Position Check <br>based on sheer strength for the rest of the Scene. 2. Speed: <br>Y our speed triples and you get 1 Additional Success at any <br>Position Check based on speed for the rest of the Scene. <br>3. Energy: Y our body is infused with pure energy and you <br>receive 3 Energy Tokens for the rest of the Scene. Y ou or <br>another nearby magic practitioner can use 1 Energy Token <br>to have 1 Additional Success when using any kind of magic. <br>Y ou can activate more than one effect of this Gift in the same <br>Scene by suffering additional Wounds. Wounds you suffer in <br>this way cannot be recovered in the current Scene.<br>This is My House (Special Gift for the Woman <br>from the Wood)<br>Requirement: Reach the village of Hosn.<br>Y ou remember this place, this is where you lived, and this <br>is where you worked as a baker. With your delicious sweets, <br>you fed the poor children of the village, but then someone <br>whose face you don’t remember poisoned what you created, <br>killing those you cared about. Y ou forgot what you did to <br>keep from succumbing to pain. Now you can decide:<br> <br> Forget what happened again.<br>In this case, deep anger will accompany you throughout your <br>stay on the island. Y ou always get 1 Additional Success when <br>you act to eradicate a threat that puts the life of a helpless <br>human at risk.<br> Remember who you were. <br>Y ou will return to be the witch of your past, but this will <br>mean profoundly changing who you are now. Permanently <br>replace your sheet with that of Katharina the Sweet Witch <br>found at the end of this Scenario.</p><p>1<br>2<br>Special<br>104<br>The Scenario <br>Hunger Island in <br>Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  Arrival at the <br>port of Vík í Mýrdal<br>It’s the same one you find on page 94. While wandering <br>around the port, the Hunters will be attacked by the <br>Maws and then will meet Berend, who will invite them to <br>the lighthouse. Gréte, left in the shadows to observe the <br>situation, will flee to Hosn to warn her brother of the arrival <br>of the Hunters.<br>End of Scene: Berend takes the Hunters to the lighthouse <br>to meet Althea. Go to the SECOND SCENE – The lighthouse.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714974,"modifiedTime":1781513714974,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"z3jM8UAckL6zxBoq","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Hunger Island - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE –  <br>The lighthouse<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: An excited Berend takes you <br>to the oldest part of the port of Vík í Mýrdal. Crates of fish <br>have been spilled in the area around the lighthouse and now <br>rot in the sun, causing a reek that makes sore vomit rise at <br>the back of your throat. Berend explains, with witty eyes, that <br>the monsters he calls Maws are drawn by the scent of humans <br>and are confused by the smell of rot. With pride, Berend <br>raises his dirty shirt and shows you a hairy torso encrusted <br>with dirt and fish guts. As he starts to pull his pants down, <br>a female voice tells him to stop. Althea, the emissary of the <br>Order who came here before you, comes out of the door of <br>the old lighthouse and yells at the poor madman who led you <br>here.<br>Place: The old lighthouse of the port that Althea and <br>Berend have fortified to keep the Maws away.<br>Time: It is late afternoon as the sun begins its descent, <br>hidden by the dense clouds fed by the fumes of the volcano.<br>Information: Althea will be grateful to the Hunters <br>for their arrival. Although the woman is extremely worn <br>by exhaustion and hunger, she will give the Hunters the <br>information on page 97. Althea will ask the Hunters to <br>accompany her to Hosn, to strike at the “leaders” of the <br>Maws and put an end to the threat they represent. It is clear <br>to the Order’s agent that the island’s stocks of both animals <br>and humans are rapidly depleting, and she fears it’s only <br>a matter of time before the Maws organize themselves to <br>set sail for the mainland. Alternatively, Althea will follow <br>the Hunters to the volcano if that’s where they intend to <br>investigate.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters leave with Althea for Hosn or <br>the Volcano. Go to SPECIAL SCENE – Along the way.<br>SPECIAL SCENE –  Along the <br>way<br>This Scene must be played every time the Hunters set out <br>on a journey. Select one of the effects on page 98.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters arrive at the village of Hosn. <br>Go to THIRD SCENE OPTION A – The village of Hosn or <br>to THIRD SCENE OPTION B – Laki, the Volcano.</p><p>3b3a<br>105</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714974,"modifiedTime":1781513714974,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"C2bxNpPaNie7RLXF","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Hunger Island - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>The village of Hosn<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You arrive at Hosn following <br>a little used farm track, convinced that your enemies are posted <br>everywhere. A series of cries and moans draws your attention. <br>In the center of the small town square, a rudimentary wooden <br>cage holds six people prisoner. They seem to be ordinary <br>villagers, emaciated and shaken by the hardships they have <br>endured. Then, the sound of footfalls resonating among the <br>semi-destroyed houses make it clear to you that your enemies <br>are practically everywhere.<br>Place: The small village of Hosn, shrouded in fog.<br>Time: It is a cold day’s dawn and the rays of the sun reflect in <br>the fog, making it look almost like a white veil.<br>Information: Gréte stayed at the village to organize the <br>defenses, while Hanse moved to the volcano. The Maws will <br>first attempt to overcome the Hunters, taking advantage of the <br>numerical superiority. <br> ◆ The weak point of the Maws, however, is to attack without <br>any strategy, running at the Hunters like rabid dogs. <br> ◆ If cornered, Gréte will be willing to compromise by <br>freeing the villagers, with the exception of Enoch.<br> ◆ If released, Ina will try to reason with Gréte, proving to be <br>an asset to the Hunters.<br> ◆ In the village, there are a total of 18 Maws, moving in <br>groups of 6.<br>End of Scene: After freeing the village, talking to prisoners, <br>or interrogating Gréte, the Hunters will clearly understand <br>that the origin of all this is in Laki, where Hanse has retreated. <br>Go to THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  Laki, the Volcano. If, on <br>the other hand, the Hunters come from the volcano, go to the</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714974,"modifiedTime":1781513714974,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"rHZrYiEfbidvZ4zS","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Hunger Island - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE – The Great Maw.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714974,"modifiedTime":1781513714974,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"C2bxNpPaNie7RLXF","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Hunger Island - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  <br> Laki, the Volcano<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Finally, the volcano is no longer <br>just a looming shadow that hangs over all of you since you <br>landed. Now, it stands out in all its grandeur, its top lost among    <br>dense clouds. The earth thrums as if following the beating of a <br>huge heart, which is nothing more than the core of the volcano <br>itself. Among the split rocks, you can see several tunnels that <br>seem to unravel inside the volcano, and grotesque and guttural <br>sounds make you realize that the frequent eruptions are not the <br>worst danger you could encounter.<br>Place: Laki, the Volcano.<br>Time: It is a cold day’s dawn and the rays of the sun reflect in <br>the fog, making it look almost like a white veil.<br>Information: The Hunters will almost immediately come <br>across several Crazed Maws. To get to the center of the <br>volcano, they will have to deal with at least 2, or find a way to <br>follow them to the tunnel where the stone is located.<br> ◆ Hanse is protecting the stone with 2 Crazed Maws to back <br>him up. The boy is willing to bargain with the Hunters for <br>the promise that they will leave the island and leave him <br>and his new people alone.<br> ◆ If cornered, Hanse will throw himself into the volcano <br>carrying the stone with him, and the Hunters will see him <br>burn in the lava.<br> ◆ Hanse will not die in the lava but, consuming all the power <br>of the stone, he will emerge a few hours later filled with <br>anger for the possibilities lost because of the Hunters.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can move to the village of Hosn <br>to save the remaining inhabitants. Go to THIRD SCENE <br>OPTION A – The village of Hosn. If, on the other hand, the <br>Hunters come from the village, go to FOURTH SCENE – The <br>Great Maw.</p><p>4<br>106</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714974,"modifiedTime":1781513714974,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"rHZrYiEfbidvZ4zS","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Hunger Island - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE –  The Great Maw<br>This Scene begins after the defeat of both siblings. Hanse, driven mad by the <br>loss of the stone, returns to Hosn as the Hunters prepare to leave. Gréte, who <br>pretended to be dead thanks to her powers, will be reunited with her brother <br>and merge with him into the Great Maw. Play the Great Maw Threat as described <br>on page 102.<br>End of Scene: Hunters manage to escape from the island or end the life of the <br>Great Maw by making it fall into the volcano. Whatever choice they make, only <br>the Hunters can end the danger the Maws represent.</p><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a capable cook and my body has a sweet smell that relaxes whoever <br>is near me. I can tell a lot about people from their food tastes. I deeply <br>hate those who hurt or bully children and the helpless.<br>•  The Sweet Witch: Y ou can spend 1 Soma to offer one of your sweets <br>to someone to make them well disposed towards you. Y ou gain 1 Additional <br>Success to convince and manipulate those who have eaten one of your sweets <br>until the end of the Scene. Y ou can decide that your dessert has an additional <br>effect based on its flavor: <br>1. Marzipan: Whoever eats it will fall into a deep sleep for several hours. <br>2. Candied fruit: The taste of the treat pushes those who are intoxicated to <br>reveal what they cherish the most. <br>3. Cinnamon: Those who eat it will feel the urgent desire to do more than <br>what they are doing, even at the expense of their duty. <br>4. Raisins: The taste of the treat pushes those who are intoxicated to reveal <br>what they hate the most.<br>Other Hunters or particularly capable individuals may require a Position <br>Check to make use of the power of your sweets.<br>I am a capable witch and when I need it, the world around me shapes <br>itself to protect and shelter me. I hate being out in the open and avoid <br>being the center of attention.<br>•  Home Sweet Home: you can spend 1 Soma to draw on your strange <br>witch powers. When you do, choose one of the following effects. <br>1. Create a shelter, for one person, perfectly camouflaged within the <br>environment. It is very difficult to discover your shelter, though some NPCs <br>can come close. At the Storyteller’s discretion, a Defense Check may be made <br>to see if you are discovered. <br>2. Change the texture of an inanimate object into a soft sweet. Y ou can turn a <br>door into marzipan or a sword into colored jelly. <br>3. Make an edible sweet and more nutritious. Whoever consumes your sweet <br>recovers 2 Soma, except yourself.<br>Katharina <br>the Sweet Witch<br>I am a witch specializing in creating magic sweets. I have always used my skills to help all the poor children <br>who cannot afford something good to eat. Giving a little joy to the poor was what warmed my heart the most. But <br>one day, a strange figure called the One Who Plots in the Shadow deceived me by poisoning what I baked with <br>so much love. That day, an entire village lost its future forever with the passing of all the children. I am aware <br>that I am not really guilty of the deaths of so many innocents, but this doesn’t lift the weight from my heart. All <br>I have left is revenge, which I will take as a Hunter of the Order against the one who, on a whim, destroyed <br>everything I cared about.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>I love human flesh, a legacy of the alien stone’s power, to which <br>I have been exposed. I can regenerate my body, and my senses are <br>incredibly sharp. I am helplessly attracted to those who have a <br>particular appearance that stimulates my appetite, such as a good <br>smell or velvety skin. <br>•  Dark Ego - Soft and Succulent Flesh:  The truth is that you <br>crave human flesh, especially when raw and taken from evil people. When <br>you inflict a Wound through violent action on someone you deem evil, and <br>if you reach an Outcome with an Increment, you may inflict 1 additional <br>Wound. Once per Scene when you consume human flesh, you recover 1 <br>Wound and the Storyteller will reveal some memories of the victim, giving <br>you contextualized information about what you are looking for..<br>Activator: Blatantly manifest your desire to devour human flesh, regardless of the consequences.<br>Equipment <br>A doll and a wooden soldier, the only memories of the <br>children I cared for / A clean dress and an apron that smells <br>of sweets / A series of incredibly sharp, small pastry knives / <br>A suitcase of fine leather that contains everything I need to <br>produce excellent desserts / A picnic tablecloth / The key to <br>my small pastry workshop. <br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714975,"modifiedTime":1781513714975,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"hunger-island","collection":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","pages":"93-108"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714975,"modifiedTime":1781513714975,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Ws1V33ckbcuhDFQn","name":"The House of Roses","pages":[{"_id":"IVs0qS0v85zzYcAt","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>The House of Roses</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> The Broken Ones</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 123-134.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/the-house-of-roses-p123-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727557,"modifiedTime":1781513727557,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MjWOrvXIzuPrhyqX","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The House of Roses - Setup</h2><p>122<br>Once upon a time…<br>The Papal State. Father Cristoforo, ministering <br>to the city of Capodimonte, wrote to the Papacy <br>to request the intervention of a group of Hunters. <br>Several years ago, the formerly abandoned <br>convent on Martana Island became the home of <br>a mysterious cult called the House of Roses. It is <br>sponsored by the rich Dionysus Gonsalva, heir to <br>the family that has always lived in Capodimonte, <br>a town on the shores of Lake Bolsena. Many <br>young girls in the area have left their families to <br>go to Martana Island, severing all ties with their <br>past. It seems that this blasphemous cult is led by <br>a mysterious priestess, but access to the island is <br>prohibited by order of the Gonsalva family. Given <br>the excellent relations between the Gonsalva <br>family and the Papacy, the Hunters must go to <br>Capodimonte and seek permission to access the <br>island.<br>A Scenario Inspired by <br>Beauty and the Beast <br>(Jeanne-Marie Leprince de <br>Beaumont)<br>The House of Roses<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Animalistic Savagery / Cult / <br>Brainwashing / Drugs / Reduced <br>Inhibitions</p><p>123<br>The story that led us here…<br>Dionysus Gonsalva is a young noble, victim of a <br>curse that has deformed his body and made him monstrous. <br>He is always in search of a bride, as he has been through <br>several over the years. The marriage has always ended in <br>blood when the bride first sees her prospective husband and <br>rejects Dionysus in horror. Bellina Cantalupo (known as <br>Bella) is a humble but ambitious servant who arrived at the <br>Gonsalva court in service to Marianna De Rossi, Dionysus’ <br>most recently deceased wife. Bella soon sensed the distress <br>of her lord and, without a second thought, worked her way <br>into his good graces to become his secret lover. Despite the <br>disgust she feels for Dionysus, Bella beguiled her lord with <br>the promise of true love. She also convinced him to move <br>to the old, abandoned monastery of Martana Island. The <br>two then founded the House of Roses, a place to welcome <br>young girls in search of a life away from the poverty that <br>plagues the current era. In the House of Roses, the young <br>novices are cared for and pampered, unaware that once <br>a month, one of them will be sacrificed to Dionysius to <br>appease his distorted need for love. Bella even arranged for <br>her two sisters, Francesca and Letizia, to join her in the cult. <br>She had always envied their beauty and planned for both of <br>them to be torn apart by her captive lover. Francesca, the <br>older sister, saw the true nature of Dionysus when he was <br>unleashed against Letizia. She escaped and now roams the <br>island, hunted by the servants of Dionysus, waiting for the <br>chance to escape.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Capodimonte. Pietro Gonsalva, head of the noble family, <br>receives more and more complaints from the population <br>due to the continuous disappearance of young girls, who <br>flee to the House of Roses in search of a comfortable life. <br>Mere months after its foundation, the House of Roses <br>has become so famous as to attract young people from all <br>over Italy. Although Pietro does not know what is really <br>happening on Martana Island, the delusional letters of <br>his son Dionysus have made him worried. Now the old <br>nobleman hopes that an outside authority (such as the <br>Hunters) will take care of the situation.<br>Francesca hides in the dense vegetation of the island, <br>unable to leave it by swimming because the waters of the <br>lake are too cold in the middle of winter. The poor fugitive <br>keeps an eye on the pier in the hope of being able to secretly <br>embark on one of the ships that, after unloading the new <br>arrivals, returns to Capodimonte. In the House of Roses, <br>Bellina is consumed with anger at her sister’s escape and <br>now has total control over Dionysus’ psyche, treating him <br>like an animal. Bellina is surrounded by faithful servants, <br>all brainwashed to serve her as a goddess, and maintains <br>control over the island thanks to a pack of trained mastiffs <br>that obey Dionysus due to his bestial curse.</p><p>1<br>124</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727558,"modifiedTime":1781513727558,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"VYvWkexOUw5mW9n7","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The House of Roses - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Capodimonte is a rich city <br>near Lake Bolsena that, thanks to the huge investments of the <br>noble Gonsalva family, has grown quite prosperous. After a <br>few minutes’ walk, you come across the church of San Carlo, <br>the smallest in the city, amidst small shops packed with busy <br>apprentices. Now you just have to decide whether to enter to <br>meet Father Cristoforo or first introduce yourself to the noble <br>Pietro Gonsalva, the regent of the city.<br>Place: The rich and prosperous city of Capodimonte.<br>Time: It is a cold morning.<br>Initial Situation: Hunters can decide who to meet and in <br>what order between the noble Pietro Gonsalva (at the city’s <br>fortress) and Father Cristoforo (in the small church of San <br>Carlo). Both men will have information about the House of <br>Roses, bringing a different point of view to the attention of <br>the Hunters.<br>Capodimonte<br>Descriptor: A rich and prosperous city protected by the Papal <br>State.<br>Pietro Gonsalva Regent of <br>Capodimonte<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have <br>managed to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being <br>in charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more <br>experienced than I am.<br>Agenda: Preserve the House of Roses because it is the first <br>place where Dionysus appears to be restrained / Not to lose the <br>advantageous agreements made with the Church.<br>Information from the conversation with Pietro:  <br>The Regent of Capodimonte will welcome the Hunters with <br>all honors, praising their importance to the Church and for <br>humanity’ salvation. Pietro is sincerely respectful of the work <br>of the Order. <br> ◆ Pietro will say that the island was once a monastery and <br>that, thanks to the efforts of his son Dionysus, it has now <br>returned to a renewed splendor.<br> ◆ Martana Island has become a place of worship, where <br>people can take refuge and contemplate God.<br> ◆ Pietro cares a lot about the House of Roses because <br>his son Dionysus is suffering from a rare disease that <br>covers his whole body with hair and, unfortunately, his <br>monstrous aspect is not accepted by society. To Pietro, it</p><p>125<br>seems the island is the only place Dionysus has ever <br>been judged for the good he can do and not for his <br>fearsome appearance.<br> ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters <br>that Pietro has no idea of what life is like on the island, <br>he has never been there and, because of the many <br>diplomatic involvements around it, he has no interest <br>in discovering more. For the reasons mentioned above, <br>Pietro will make sure the Hunters understand that the <br>House of Roses must remain active.<br> ◆ With great generosity, Pietro will offer the Hunters a <br>boat that will take them to the island in the afternoon.<br>Father Cristoforo<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a humble provincial priest and I have <br>been responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas <br>for years. <br>Agenda: I have reason to believe that the House of Roses is <br>a place of blasphemy and damnation, so I want the Church <br>to investigate.<br>Information from the conversation with <br>Cristoforo: The humble priest will welcome the Hunters <br>in the small church of San Carlo. The man will show <br>reverence to the work of the Order and will seem aware of <br>who the Hunters really are.<br> ◆ Cristoforo will say that the island once was a <br>monastery where the residents dedicated themselves to <br>blasphemous rites. The Church intervened by putting <br>them all at the stake.<br> ◆ Martana Island is a name on the lips of many young <br>people, who tell of a place of feasts and pleasures far <br>from the severe but holy eye of God. Many young women <br>go out of their way to get to sail to the island. <br> ◆ Cristoforo taught the ways of God to the unfortunate <br>Dionysus, being troubled by the savagery that the young <br>man struggled to control. <br> ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters <br>that Cristoforo does not really know what is happening on <br>the island, but he is firmly convinced that it is nothing good.<br> ◆ Trying not to be overheard by prying ears, Cristoforo will <br>tell the Hunters that a couple of faithful friends have a small <br>boat and can take the Hunters to the island at night, landing <br>on a little-used beach. <br>Martana Island<br>Descriptor: A small island in the center of Lake Bolsena. Covered <br>mostly by dense vegetation, the island includes a sanctuary, a <br>small pier, and a mansion recently built by the Gonsalvas.<br>There are five locations available on the island:<br> ◆ The Pier: Where all ships arriving from Capodimonte dock. <br>The pier is under the control of Bella and her worshippers. <br>If the Hunters accept Pietro Gonsalva’s transportation offer, <br>they will arrive there in the late afternoon.<br> ◆ The White Beach: A small beach of rocks and earth to the <br>east of the island. It is located on the opposite side of the <br>island from the few inhabited places. If the Hunters accept <br>Father Cristoforo’s offer of transportation, they will reach <br>the beach at night.<br> ◆ The Sanctuary: All the young people who have become <br>prisoners of the House of Roses live here.<br> ◆ The Mansion: The House of Roses is a sumptuous villa that <br>Dionysus had built for Bella.</p><p>126<br> ◆ The Forest: A large wooded area where Dionysus’ <br>Mastiffs roam. In the thick of the forest, there is a <br>mass grave where Bella dumps the bodies of the <br>Beast’s unfortunate victims.<br>The Pier<br>Descriptor: A small pier with a watchtower.<br>Information: At the pier there are always 8 Servants, <br>armed and ready to welcome every arrival. In the guard <br>tower there are 6 other Servants equipped with firearms.<br>Bella’s Servants <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are young people in the service of Bella <br>and we are trained to defend the House <br>of Roses. <br>Agenda: Follow all of Bella’s <br>orders to the letter. <br>Gift – For Our Lady:  The Servants are brainwashed <br>and totally dependent on Bella. Every attempt to scare or <br>mentally manipulate them receives 2 Penalties. If Bella <br>is targeted by a threat, once per Exchange, a Servant can <br>sacrifice themselves to take the hit in her place. <br>The White Beach<br>Descriptor: A small beach of pebbles and earth hidden <br>among the dense vegetation.<br>Information: Docking at the beach without the <br>necessary precautions will attract 1d6+2 Mastiffs.<br>The Forest<br>Descriptor: A large wooded area that almost entirely <br>covers Martana Island.<br>Information: The forest is overrun by mastiffs loyal to <br>Dionysus. Avoiding them requires overcoming the Pack of <br>Mastiffs Threat. In case of a Failure, 8 Mastiffs will appear <br>and surround the intruders. At the center of the forest is <br>a mass grave where the bodies of Dionysus’ victims are <br>dumped. Francesca hides in the pit to escape the hungry <br>dogs.<br>Threat – Pack of Mastiffs<br>OL Medium 5 <br>Descriptor: We patrol the forest, looking for intruders. No <br>one can escape our sense of smell.</p><p>127<br>Dionysus’ Mastiffs<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our <br>leader, Dionysus.<br>Agenda: Hunt down any intruders arriving on the island.<br>Gift – Pack:  Any action taken while surrounded by 2 <br>or more Mastiffs receives 1 Penalty. A Mastiff can use its <br>action to howl and alert Dionysus, who will arrive within <br>2 Exchanges.<br>Francesca Cantalupo<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.<br>Agenda: Flee the island to return to my father / Avenge <br>Letizia’s death and punish Bellina for always being a selfish, <br>jealous child.<br>The Sanctuary<br>Descriptor: An ancient monastery converted into a small <br>pleasure town. <br>Information: 20 Handmaids and 10 Servants are <br>always present in the Sanctuary. All the inhabitants of the <br>Sanctuary live surrounded by food and pleasures of the <br>flesh, in a state of constant and perverse ecstasy. Bella adds <br>drugs to both food and drinks so that the inhabitants of the <br>Sanctuary lose their inhibitions.<br>Threat – The Food of the Gods<br>OL Medium 5 <br>Descriptor: All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a <br>powerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.<br>Gift – The Drug of the True Self:  Whoever eats food <br>treated with this powerful drug loses all inhibition. Anyone <br>who fails the Defense Check to resist the effect receives 2 <br>Drug Tokens. During a Scene, the Storyteller can spend 1 <br>Drug Token to activate one of the following effects. 1. The <br>True Self: Immediately activates the Hunter’s Dark Ego <br>without them suffering the Wound generated by not using <br>the Activator. 2. Dulled Senses: The Storyteller decides <br>what type of Outcome the Hunter is aiming for after they <br>have declared an action. <br>Bella’s Handmaids <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are <br>ready to have a good time – anytime.<br>Agenda: We have tasted happiness in the House of Roses <br>and we will not allow anyone to take us back to our former, <br>miserable lives.</p><p>128<br>The Mansion also known as the <br>House of Roses<br>Descriptor: A large and rich mansion, with a wide garden, <br>a hedge maze, and beautiful red roses.<br>Information: Bella lives in the Mansion where 8 Servants <br>are executing any of their lady’s wishes. Dionysus lives in <br>the cellars of the estate and only goes out at night or when <br>his Mastiffs get his attention.    <br>Threat – Hedge Labyrinth<br>OL Medium 5 <br>Descriptor: A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that <br>extends throughout the estate garden. <br>Gift – Secret Passage:  Bellina and Dionysus know a <br>series of secret passages to avoid wasting time in the maze. <br>Anyone else might need several hours to negotiate it.   <br>Bellina Cantalupo known as Bella<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a cunning manipulator and the only queen of the House of Roses. I <br>take advantage of the power I wield whenever I have the chance.<br>Agenda: Increase the influence of the House of Roses at any cost / Getting rid of <br>Dionysus, but without destroying the House of Roses.<br>Gift – Manipulative:  During a Scene, if Bella has enough time to talk to a <br>subject, she will learn a secret about them, such as a Descriptor or <br>their Gift. Bella is immune to any kind of mental manipulation <br>or fear. <br>Gift – My Beast:  If Bella is in danger, Dionysus will come <br>to her rescue within 1 Exchange. To help Bella, Dionysus <br>can free himself from any kind of impediment, whether <br>physical or mental. Nothing can stop Dionysus, who <br>will break through doors and walls if necessary.</p><p>129<br>Dioniso Gonsalva called the <br>Beast<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a young man afflicted by a curse <br>that turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent <br>keeps my incredible ferocity in check.<br>Agenda: I would like to live alone with Bella <br>in this paradise, and I only tolerate the House <br>of Roses for the sake of my love for her / I <br>would like to show the full extent of my love <br>to Bella, but until she gives herself to me, I <br>will have to take my frustration out on <br>her handmaids.<br>Gift – The Beast:  Dionysus can <br>act twice during an Exchange. When <br>moving, Dionysus can jump up to thirty <br>feet and easily destroy any obstacle. <br>When acting to save Bella, Dionysus <br>increases his Opposition Level by 1.</p><p>130<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario there are five Events. As a Storyteller, feel free <br>to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunters.<br>If the Hunters capture Bella:  the Lady of the House of <br>Roses will threaten to unleash Dionysus’ wrath on all the <br>innocents on the island. Bella will demand that the Hunters <br>release her, while trying to negotiate a deal that works for <br>everyone.<br>If the Hunters kill Dionysus:  Bella will thank them by <br>telling them that it was all the fault of the mad nobleman <br>who forced her to do everything. Her aim is to escape the <br>judgment of the Church by passing herself off as a victim.<br>If the Hunters find Francesca:  the young woman will <br>describe how all the Handmaids ignore what truly happens <br>to Bella’s chosen ones. Francesca will tell the Hunters who <br>Bellina really is, and how she brainwashed everyone on the <br>island thanks to her position of power and the drugs in the <br>food.<br>If the Hunters officially show up at the pier:  Bella <br>will welcome them with all honors by offering them food <br>and drinks. Bella’s purpose is to gather information about <br>the newcomers and then feed them to Dionysus one by one.<br>If the Hunters accuse Bella or Dionysus:  Bella will <br>seek an advantageous agreement by mentioning that the <br>Gonsalva family is one of the greatest supporters of the <br>Papacy, and that a scandal could end the huge subsidies that <br>Pietro regularly pays to Rome. <br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the The <br>House of Roses Scenario and can be acquired once the <br>requirements are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario <br>Gift and if they acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the <br>previous one.<br>Gift – Faithful Mastiffs<br>Requirement: Have defeated one or more of Dionysus’ <br>Mastiffs.<br>Y ou defeated the Mastiffs, proving you are a worthy pack <br>leader. Y ou gain 1 Mastiff who follows you as a faithful <br>companion. Y ou can spend 1 Soma to assign a task to your <br>Mastiff for the rest of the Scene. 1. Find: The Mastiff can <br>track an object or a person if you are able to provide it with <br>a sample of its smell; 2. Defend: The Mastiff stands in your <br>defense, granting you 1 Additional Success in all Defense <br>Checks. In case of an Outcome with a Cost, the Mastiff  <br>will die taking the blow in your place as a Cost; 3. Attack: <br>The Mastiff attacks the enemy you point to, reducing their <br>Opposition Level by 1 for the course of the Exchange. Each <br>time you use this effect, roll a die. With 4+ the Mastiff is <br>killed in the action. If your Mastiff is killed, you can get <br>another one at the beginning of the next Scene.<br>Gift - Uncovering Deceptions<br>Requirement: You know how to expose a charlatan and lay <br>bare lies.<br>All NPCs who possess a Descriptor, Gift, or Agenda that has <br>to do with lying or deceiving others reduce their Opposition <br>Level by 1 in your presence. When you’re around, you also <br>weaken their followers: once per Scene you can prevent a <br>subject from using a Gift that depends on using or sacrificing <br>a follower.</p><p>1<br>2a<br>131<br>The Scenario The <br>House of Roses in <br>Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  Arrival at <br>Capodimonte<br>It’s the same one you find on page 124. The Hunters will <br>go first to interview Pietro Gonsalva and then to Father <br>Cristoforo.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can decide whether to land on <br>the island through the passage offered by Pietro, go to</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727558,"modifiedTime":1781513727558,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sJmOYGdbSRrWI67O","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The House of Roses - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION A – The pier. Or land secretly <br>thanks to the help of Cristoforo, go to SECOND SCENE <br>OPTION B – The White Beach.</p><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION A <br>– The pier<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: In less than an hour’s sailing, <br>you can already see the shape of Martana Island looming in <br>front of you. The boat arrives in a small covered port, where <br>you find a large group of men with smiling faces waiting for <br>you, though it’s difficult to ignore the weapons they carry. <br>A young girl with wavy brown hair seems to be the person <br>in charge, and when you get off the boat, she greets you, <br>smiling. “I am Bella Cantalupo, and I serve my lord Dionysus <br>Gonsalva so that the House of Roses may be a place of peace <br>and prayer. Please be our guests for at least one night. ” Bella <br>beckons you to follow her to what appears to be a completely <br>renovated monastery.<br>Place: Martana Island’s pier.<br>Time: It is almost time for dinner.<br>Information: Bella will be extremely helpful with the <br>Hunters, trying to answer all their questions. The woman’s <br>goal is to impede the investigation and pass the House of <br>Roses off as a place of worship and peace.<br> ◆ If the Hunters ask her about Dionysus, Bella will say <br>that her master shuns situations in which there are <br>many people because of his appearance. Bella takes <br>care of everything, but if the Hunters want to, she will <br>set up an interview with Dionysus.<br> ◆ Bella will highlight the peace and prosperity in which <br>servants and handmaids live, and all the young people <br>will be helpful and happy.<br> ◆ Bella will invite the Hunters to stay for the night and <br>organize a banquet in their honor. The Hunters will <br>be asked to stay within Sanctuary so as not to risk <br>provoking the many mastiffs that Dionysus breeds in <br>the forest.<br> ◆ The Mansion is reserved for Dionysus, and for this <br>reason it is inaccessible to the Hunters. Sneaking into <br>it, you will find ample supplies of Mandrake and other <br>herbs useful to produce drugs. <br> ◆ Bella will watch the Hunters closely, always maintaining <br>her fake, friendly smile. <br>End of Scene:  After talking to Bella and seeing the <br>Sanctuary, the Hunters will be invited to a banquet set up <br>just for them. Go to THIRD SCENE OPTION A – Welcome <br>guests.</p><p>3a 3b<br>2b<br>132</p><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION B  – <br>The White Beach<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You land on a small beach of <br>pebbles and mud. As soon as you step off the boat, the sailors <br>hastily set sail once more, making the sign of the cross. Only a <br>few seconds pass before you hear growls and howls. Apparently, <br>a wolf or dog pack is moving towards you, attracted by your <br>smell.<br>Place: A small beach on Martana Island.<br>Time: It is almost time for dinner.<br>Information: A group of 8 Mastiffs will try to intercept <br>the Hunters and, if the clash begins, they will immediately <br>howl to summon Dionysus. The beastly lord of the island <br>will attack without hesitation but will flee after suffering 2 <br>Wounds. If, on the other hand, the Hunters manage to hide <br>from the pack of Mastiffs, they will see Dionysus coming and <br>will be able to observe him in all his savagery. Dionysus will <br>remain for a few minutes before leaving and returning to the <br>Mansion.<br>End of Scene:  Having faced or avoided the Mastiffs, the <br>Hunters will come across the mass grave, go to THIRD <br>SCENE OPTION B – Unwanted guests.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727559,"modifiedTime":1781513727559,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"G2d9JpOQNjce1jlz","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The House of Roses - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>Welcome guests<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The banquet Bella has set up <br>for you is sumptuous to say the least. Wine and delicacies of <br>all kinds cover the great table of the Sanctuary, while around <br>you, servants and handmaids dance and sip wine, indulging <br>in the pleasures of the evening. Even Bella seems particularly <br>euphoric, inviting you to enjoy the fine things her generous lord <br>Dionysus has to offer. <br>Place: The Sanctuary of the island.<br>Time: The sun has just gone down.<br>Information: Bella will try to drug the Hunters to lower <br>their defenses and discover how much of a threat they are. If <br>the Hunters insist on meeting Dionysus, Bella will ask that <br>only one of them go, since her lord is not accustomed to being <br>seen by many people at once. If the Hunters consent, the <br>chosen one will be taken to the Mansion’s rose garden, where <br>Dionysus will attack, trying to kill them. If the Hunters keep <br>a low-profile during dinner, at some point Bella will be called <br>away by a servant to deal with an emergency. The Hunters <br>will be able to see concern in the eyes of the young woman, <br>since Dionysus is having one of his fits and needs to consume <br>one of the handmaids to appease himself. Bella will take a <br>girl with her, saying goodbye to the Hunters. Following Bella <br>will require overcoming two groups of 8 Servants, which the <br>woman will put on the road between the Sanctuary and the <br>Mansion.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters now clearly understand that <br>something dark animates Bella’s actions, and they arrive at <br>the Mansion to witness the sacrifice, go to the FOURTH <br>SCENE – The sacrifice.</p><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B – <br>Unwanted Guests<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You have overcome the <br>terrible Mastiffs patrolling the forest and, as you cross the <br>rugged woodland, a nauseating smell draws your attention. A <br>little more than ten meters away, a large grave contains the <br>bodies of a multitude of young girls, all horribly mutilated, as <br>if a ferocious creature had devoured them. Suddenly, one of the <br>girls seems to be moving, making a soft cry.</p><p>4<br>5<br>133<br>Place: The mass grave in the middle of the island’s Forest.<br>Time: It is night, and a soft moonlight filters through the <br>branches of the trees.<br>Information: It will be possible to find Francesca within <br>the pit, looking worn and on the edge of madness. The young <br>woman will describe all the crimes Bellina has committed and <br>how Letizia was sacrificed to the fury of Dionysus. The young <br>woman’s only wish is to run away but, if the Hunters play on <br>her anger, she will ask to follow them to avenge her dead sister. <br>Francesca’s voice is known to the Mastiffs, and within a short <br>time, a pack of 8 will reach the pit, led by Dionysus. In the <br>event of a confrontation, the beastly noble will do everything <br>he can to kill Francesca. As in the previous clash, Dionysus <br>will flee as soon as he receives the second Wound.<br>End of Scene: Once Bellina’s faults have been discovered, the <br>Hunters can move to the Mansion to capture her. Go to THE</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727559,"modifiedTime":1781513727559,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"xn7Pn1JWZN0SzkP6","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The House of Roses - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE – The sacrifice.</p><p>FOURTH SCENE – The sacrifice<br>There are two ways to get to this Scene.<br>From the banquet: The Hunters follow Bella and catch her <br>red-handed as she prepares to feed Dionysus an unsuspecting <br>handmaid.<br>From the grave:  The Hunters arrive at the garden of <br>the Mansion led by Francesca just as Bella prepares to feed <br>Dionysus an unsuspecting handmaid.<br>Place: The rose garden of the Mansion.<br>Time: It is night, and only the full moon illuminates the small <br>labyrinth of hedges and roses.<br>Information: The ritual consists of bringing the handmaid <br>to the center of the maze of hedges, and then letting Dionysus <br>unleash his desires. Only Bella and Dionysus are present at the <br>rite, since none of the servants or handmaids must discover <br>the truth. If the Hunters intervene, Bella will not hesitate to <br>unleash Dionysus against them. While they battle, she will <br>flee to the Sanctuary to stir up all the servants and handmaids <br>against the Hunters, accusing them of having been sent by the <br>Papacy to end the House of Roses.<br>End of Scene:  After facing Dionysus, the Hunters must <br>handle Bella who sends all the inhabitants of the island against <br>them. Go to SCENE FIVE – Face to face.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727559,"modifiedTime":1781513727559,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TKcr1U9IFUKXb7TB","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The House of Roses - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE – Face to face<br>This Scene can have many variables, based on what the <br>Hunters have discovered so far. There will be 20 Servants and <br>20 Handmaids in the Scene.<br>Place: The Sanctuary.<br>Time: It is late at night and the only light is cast by the banquet <br>bonfires.<br>Information: Bella will use all her influence to cast the <br>Hunters in a bad light, also accusing them of the attempted <br>(or successful) murder of Dionysus, the one who has been <br>supporting everyone at the House of Roses. Bella will make <br>the Hunters understand that she is willing to come to terms <br>with them, but her power of manipulation is very strong and <br>she can do with the innocents who live on the island as she <br>likes.<br>End of Scene: Bella will be determined not to lose the power <br>she has gained and has an entire island at her command. The <br>Hunters will have to play their cards well to put an end to the <br>House of Roses once and for all.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727559,"modifiedTime":1781513727559,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","collection":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","pages":"123-134"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727559,"modifiedTime":1781513727559,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gHuSlF7zmnDzDN2C","name":"I Don't Believe","pages":[{"_id":"VOmvuFkJYnfbR1rI","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>I Don't Believe</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> The Broken Ones</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 81-92.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/i-dont-believe-p81-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710167,"modifiedTime":1781513710167,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LFkPpyDuCd2G48Kv","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Don't Believe - Setup</h2><p>80<br>Once upon a time…<br>London’s outskirts. Among the fumes and vapors <br>of newly-built factories, the disappearance <br>of several children has led to widespread <br>discontent among the workers. However, it <br>is only after the disappearance of Gwendolyn <br>Carnarvon, daughter of a titled noble, that the <br>royal family itself decided to turn to the Order. <br>Strange rumors are circulating in the suburbs <br>of London, where it seems that a young gang of <br>hooligans is committing violent acts to slow the <br>creeping spread of modernity, particularly in <br>the form of heartless factories. The Crown has <br>been deeply terrified by the macabre discovery <br>made by police looking into reports of violence <br>in the streets. According to rumors, factory <br>guards had engaged in a clash with the young <br>terrorists. The Crown investigators who tracked <br>down the battlefield were confronted with a <br>scene of unbelievable violence featuring broken, <br>bloody limbs and burst hearts inside shredded <br>rib cages. In great secrecy, the investigation <br>was shortly thereafter entrusted to the Hunters <br>of the Order with the aim of shedding light on <br>the danger that threatens the city and bringing <br>young Carnarvon to safety.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Peter <br>and Wendy (J. M. Barrie)<br>I Don’t Believe<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Kidnapping / Terrorism</p><p>81<br>The story that led us here…<br>A powerful fairy, known as the Cauldron Fae, has <br>been residing in London since time immemorial, long <br>before the city became what it is now. Under the false <br>identity of a personable purveyor of pots, she has lived in <br>secret on grounds she considers sacred: a series of caves and <br>galleries under the gardens of the Kensington Palace. The <br>Cauldron Fae is bothered by the modernization overtaking <br>London, slowly poisoning the clear air of the city with <br>smoke and stink. The fairy has begun to surround herself <br>with young orphans and misfits, creating a gang of ruthless <br>killers ready to do anything to please her. At the head of the <br>gang is Pietrik, a young Eastern immigrant who watched his <br>little sister die of fatigue, crushed by inhumane shifts at the <br>factory. Pietrik’s sole purpose in life is now to undermine <br>industrialization. The Cauldron Fae gave Pietrik, as her <br>most trusted servant, a magical object able to animate <br>his shadow so that he can more ably be her servant and <br>guardian. When a group of Crown investigators found the <br>secret passage from the slums to the Kensington Gardens, <br>the Cauldron Fae joined Pietrik on the field, unleashing her <br>great powers. The Cauldron Fae can control the Magic of <br>Disbelief, which allows her to imbue words with truth, but <br>only when expressing concepts of denial. By pronouncing <br>“I don’t believe in guards, ” the bodies of her enemies <br>twisted and then exploded, destroyed by devastating magic. <br>The only way to kill the Cauldron Fae is to use her own <br>magic against her, pronouncing the formula “I don’t believe <br>Mtyrya exists. ” Only Pietrik, however, knows her true name. <br>The young man fell in love with Gwendolyn and, after an <br>initial friendship, decided to kidnap her because she was <br>about to leave for Wales. As a prisoner in the Kensington <br>Gardens, the girl fears for her life, but she is perhaps the <br>only one who can lead Pietrik to reason.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Pietrik is the leader of his gang, the Lost Boys. They are out <br>of control, striking at a different business in London every <br>night. Only Gwendolyn’s entreaties can dampen the young <br>rebel’s bloodlust. The Cauldron Fae is harnessing power <br>for her greatest spell yet, which will be: “I do not believe <br>that there are people in London. ” The fairy’s goal is to get <br>rid of all the unwelcome humans in her beloved home <br>(including the Lost Boys), saving only Pietrik, to whom she <br>has become attached. To succeed, however, the fairy needs <br>power, which can only be generated by the passionate spirit <br>of young people rebelling against oppressive modernity. <br>For this reason, the Cauldron Fae encourages Pietrik and <br>his followers to strike London’s businesses more and more <br>often. Around the city have been engraved the Seals of the <br>fairy, and only those who already possess one can see the <br>others. The Lost Boys use theirs to activate the other Seals, <br>tap into the Cauldron Fae’s power, and perform small feats <br>of magic.<br>Distraught by the disappearance of his daughter, George <br>Carnarvon sent his best agents into the city. Most <br>disappeared and the remains of the few who were found <br>had been torn by savage wounds. Only at that point was <br>Carnavon willing to admit that the Hunters had skills his <br>men lacked and that made them uniquely suited to confront <br>occult powers. George is concerned for his daughter’s life, <br>and the fact that no one asked for a ransom makes him fear <br>the worst for Gwendolyn.</p><p>1<br>82</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710167,"modifiedTime":1781513710167,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"z1tJrMoHH8SHd9Kw","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Don't Believe - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You have just arrived in <br>London but, despite the exhaustion of your recent journey, <br>Lord Carnarvon has peremptorily summoned you. Tucked <br>away in one of the great homes in the city center, you find <br>yourself at the table with a fifty-year-old nobleman. The <br>puffy, dark circles around his eyes and his pale face leave you <br>with the impression that your host is very concerned about <br>what is happening in London.<br>Place: The London villa of the Carnarvon family.<br>Time: It is the late afternoon of a gloomy autumn day. <br>Initial Situation: George will update the Hunters with <br>all that happened so far. The nobleman will not hide his <br>deep concern for the fate of his daughter Gwendolyn.<br>Information: From the interview with George, the <br>Hunters will obtain the following information.<br> ◆ London is under attack by a large gang of young rebels. <br>The boys, all between the ages of ten and sixteen, hit <br>the most prosperous activities of the city, causing <br>serious accidents, damaging the tools and machinery <br>and, often, even the workers. The gang exhibits a <br>clear penchant for rebellion, focused on the nascent <br>industrial hub of London.<br> ◆ George’s sixteen-year-old daughter, Gwendolyn, was <br>abducted two days ago. The young woman has always <br>been a little rebellious but had never openly revolted <br>against her family. George fears that she has approached <br>the gang of youngsters driven by curiosity and that she <br>has been taken by them against her will. No ransom <br>demand has been made for the young woman, and that <br>makes George fear the worst. A desperate father before <br>anything else, Lord Carnavon will make it clear that <br>finding his daughter is more important to him than the <br>fate of the entire city.<br> ◆ After the clash that ended in a bloodbath the night <br>before, it is clear that the young rioters have something <br>occult on their side. Basil, the only survivor of the <br>attack, said that afterward the young attackers literally <br>disappeared through one of the walls. <br>At the end of the interview, George will be available to lead <br>the Hunters to several places:<br> ◆ To Gwendolyn’s rooms inside the palace, where the <br>Hunters can search for clues to the disappearance of <br>the young woman and interrogate her personal maid: <br>Joanna.<br> ◆ At the Sirens’ Inn, in the lower neighborhoods of <br>London, where Basil rests to recover from his injuries.<br> ◆ At the Skullem Factory, a shipyard that George fears <br>will be the next target of the young rioters.<br>Note: George will be as helpful as possible to the Hunters, <br>but it will be clear that the man is psychologically and <br>physically worn out by the events of the last days. The <br>Hunters can decide whether to keep him by their side or <br>not.<br>Note: In this Scenario, Pietrik and the Lost Boys Gang <br>can use the power of the Seals that the Cauldron Fae has <br>engraved all over London. At least one Seal, to be activated <br>at will, is always present in all the Places of the Scenario.</p><p>83<br>Threat – Seal of the Cauldron Fae<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic <br>of the Cauldron Fae.<br>Gift – Seals Everywhere:  At least one Seal of the <br>Cauldron Fae is present in all the Places of the Scenario. <br>Whoever possesses the Gang Seal or Personal Seal Gift  <br>can activate the effect of the Seal of the Cauldron Fae as an <br>additional action; this allows them to teleport to another <br>place featuring a Seal. The Seals are invisible to the human <br>eye and can be used only by those who have a tattooed eye <br>on their hand, placing said tattoo in front of the right eye. <br>Those who use magic can detect the presence of a Seal, but <br>the Seal of Disbelief Scenario Gift is necessary to activate it. <br>Note: Some Places feature more than one Seal to grant <br>the Lost Boys more narrative options in case the Hunters <br>manage to impede access to a Seal or negate the Gift. <br>George Carnarvon<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my <br>service to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. <br>I fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my <br>daughter’s abduction.<br>Agenda: Stop the gang of rebels that plagues London, but <br>more than anything else find my beloved daughter Gwendolyn.<br>Carnarvon House<br>Descriptor: A rich and large mansion in the heart of <br>London.<br>Joanna called Nana the Servant<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal <br>servant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I <br>am as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.<br>Information: Joanna will tell the Hunters that she often <br>heard Gwendolyn chatting with a boy in her room, but <br>when she came in to figure out who it was, she never found <br>anyone. Gwendolyn has always avoided revealing the boy’s <br>identity, convincing Nana that he was some noble son of <br>a good family in the city. Searching Gwendolyn’s room, <br>the Hunters will find some poppy petals under the bed. <br>Nana will say that those flowers can only be found in the <br>Kensington Gardens in London.<br>Seals: There is only one Seal in the Carnarvon villa, <br>inscribed on the east wall of Gwendolyn’s room.</p><p>84<br>The Cauldron Fae’s Lair<br>Descriptor: An extensive maze of caves and galleries stretching beneath all of <br>Kensington’s Gardens. Within it, all kinds of plants and flowers grow luxuriantly <br>thanks to the Cauldron Fae’s power.<br>Threat – Nature Rises Up<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae <br>exposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to <br>block those who walk without their lady’s approval.<br>Mtyrya the Fairy also called the <br>Cauldron Fae<br>OL Hard 7 – Main NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks <br>to my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.<br>Agenda: Prevent humans from covering my beloved land with dirty, stinking factories / Save <br>Pietrik from the punishment I plan to inflict upon London.<br>Gift – The Magic of Disbelief:  As an action, the Cauldron Fae can formulate a magic <br>sentence including the fragment I don’t believe and make its effect concrete. For example, <br>“I don’t believe in gravity” would allow her to fly, while “I don’t believe the Hunters of the <br>Order exist” would allow her to hurt the Hunters in an attempt to make them disappear. <br>If the statement does not have offensive effects, the duration of the power is generally for <br>the entire Scene. If, on the other hand, the effect is likely to harm a target, it will inflict <br>1 Wound without the possibility of attempting a Defense Check. Those who use magic can <br>try to counteract the Magic of Disbelief, and preventing Mtyrya from speaking words would <br>automatically cancel the Gift’s effect.</p><p>85<br>Gift – Ancient Fairy:  The Cauldron Fae is immortal as <br>long as her beloved plants thrive under the Kensington <br>Gardens. The true focus of her power is the rebellious spirit <br>of her young servants. The fairy starts the Scenario with <br>3 Power Tokens and can spend 1 to return from death, <br>mending all the Wounds she has suffered. Each time a <br>factory or equivalent is destroyed in retaliation against <br>modernity, she receives 1 Power Token. The Cauldron <br>Fae can spend 4 Power Tokens to unleash all her power <br>and apply the effect of the Magic of Disbelief Gift to all of <br>London.<br>London’s Slums<br>Descriptor: Wretched alleys and houses where all the poor <br>of London live.<br>Information: In the slums, you can always find 1d6+6 <br>members of the Lost Boys Gang. When he’s not on a <br>mission or at Gwendolyn’s, Pietrik is here too.<br>Seals: Almost every main street in the slums has a Seal <br>somewhere.<br>The Sirens’ Inn<br>Descriptor: A dirty inn in the lower neighborhoods, hiding <br>a clandestine stall. Poor people and prostitutes flock inside to <br>find a roof to rest under.<br>Information: Basil resides at the inn because it is the <br>only one he can afford with the low salary provided by the <br>Carnarvon family. The man will badmouth his employer (if <br>not present) and will tell the Hunters that his companions <br>were literally ripped apart before exploding horribly. The <br>youngsters’ leader (a boy with typical Eastern European <br>features) pronounced the words “I don’t believe in guards” <br>right before the bloodbath. Basil is the only one who <br>wasn’t affected, but he hurt his leg falling down while <br>fleeing (a detail he omitted during George’s account) and is <br>determined to leave London as soon as he can walk again.<br>Pietrik has been watching Basil since he came to the inn, and <br>the Hunters will notice the young man (which corresponds <br>to Basil’s description) after some time there. If cornered, <br>Pietrik will escape thanks to the power of the Seal.<br>Seals: There are two Seals in the Sirens’ Inn, one in the <br>hallway in front of Basil’s room and the other in the main <br>hall near the front door.<br>Basil the Survivor<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a coward only concerned with making <br>ends meet. <br>Agenda: To get back on my feet and escape from London, <br>away from rebels and magic.</p><p>86<br>Pietrik<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with <br>all my strength.<br>Agenda: Destroy all the factories to avenge my sister’s death / Convince Gwendolyn to <br>join my gang because I have fallen in love with her. <br>Gift – The Needle of Living Shadows: Thanks to the power of the magic needle <br>the Cauldron Fae gave him, once per Scene Pietrik can separate the shadow from <br>his body and make it act like an NPC with its own profile. The shadow has 1 <br>Wound and can slip through the smallest crack. <br>Gift – Personal Seal: Pietrik has the Seal of Disbelief tattooed on the palm <br>of his hand, so once per Scene, he can activate the Gift The Magic of Disbelief <br>(page 84). As with the Gang Seal Gift (page 87), Pietrik can activate any <br>Seal present in London. <br>The Skullem Factory<br>Descriptor: A large shipyard in which metal components for ships are <br>being assembled.<br>Information: Inside the factory, there are two large industrial <br>ovens for metal welding. The goal of the Lost Boys is to blow <br>them up by throwing the magic berries that Pietrik has given <br>out into them. The raid will take place at night and involves 10 <br>Lost Boys, in addition to Pietrik. <br>Seals: The only Seal in the area of the Skullem Factory is <br>located in the alley at the back of the building.</p><p>87<br>The Gang of the Lost Boys<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are young rebels who have lost everything <br>and are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.<br>Agenda: To help Pietrik in his plan for the destruction of <br>London. <br>Gift – Gang Seal:  Each gang member has a tattooed eye <br>on their right hand that allows them to see and use the Seals <br>of the Cauldron Fae scattered throughout London.<br>Gift – Rioter:  Each gang member increases his OL by <br>1 when acting with the support of at least one teammate. <br>Each member has a magic berry that they can throw which <br>will explode on contact, inflicting 1 Wound on all targets <br>within several feet. A Defense Check allows a target to leap <br>away from the blast zone.    <br>Kensington Gardens<br>Descriptor: A large green area in the heart of London. <br>Access to the gardens is prohibited due to ongoing <br>maintenance work. <br>Information: The Kensington Gardens have been long <br>abandoned because the Cauldron Fae uses her magic to <br>create unending problems for the gardeners. No one has <br>entered the gardens for over a year and Pietrik has used an <br>old gardeners’ house as a prison to keep Gwendolyn locked <br>up. The girl hasn’t tried to escape and hopes, so far in vain, <br>to convince Pietrik to give up on his destructive plans. <br>It is possible to descend through a well in <br>the eastern part of the park to access the <br>Cauldron Fae’s Lair. <br>Seals: The Gardens are literally full of <br>Seals.<br>Gwendolyn<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC  <br>(1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the young heir of <br>the Carnarvon family, but I dream <br>of a life of travel and freedom, <br>exploring the world. I am good at <br>telling stories, and that is how I <br>got closer to Pietrik.<br>Agenda: To convince Pietrik <br>to desist from his revenge. <br>I understand how much <br>pain his heart holds and <br>I would like to welcome <br>him into my family to <br>give him a different <br>future.</p><p>88<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>If the Cauldron Fae reaches 4 Power Tokens:  she <br>will be ready to kill all humans in London but will not do so <br>until she has secured Pietrik safely in her lair.<br>If Pietrik understands the true objective of the <br>Cauldron Fae: he will betray his mistress to try to save <br>Gwendolyn and the Lost Boys.<br>If the Hunters free Gwendolyn: the young woman will <br>tell the sad tale of Pietrik’s past, trying to make the Hunters <br>understand that the boy acts out of resentment and not true <br>evil.<br>If the Hunters capture one of the Lost Boys:  if put <br>under pressure, he will reveal that the whole gang follows <br>Pietrik’s lead and he is the only one who knows the identity <br>of the sorceress who has bestowed powers on everyone. <br>If the Hunters use Gwendolyn as bait for Pietrik:  <br>the young man will give up any involvement with the gang <br>to be with his beloved. <br>If the Lost Boys succeed in destroying the Skullem <br>Factory: one of them will be injured in the explosion and <br>can be captured by the Hunters. <br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the I Don’t <br>Believe Scenario and can be acquired once the conditions <br>are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario Gift and if <br>they acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the previous <br>one.<br>Seal of Disbelief<br>Requirement: Capture or eliminate a member of the Lost <br>Boys.<br>Y ou studied the strange Seal that unites the entire gang <br>of young rebels and created one just like it on your hand. <br>When you bring your hand over your right eye you can see <br>the Seals of the Cauldron Fae engraved throughout London. <br>By spending 1 Soma you can cross a Seal to get to another <br>Seal whose location you know. Thanks to the Seal, you can <br>perform a Defense Check to prevent the Magic of Disbelief <br>from having an effect on you. <br>Support of a Lord <br>Requirement: Save Gwendolyn from Pietrik’s clutches.<br>Y ou saved the young heir to the Carnarvon family and for <br>this, you were given a medallion bearing the family coat <br>of arms. Receive 1 Additional Success when you use the <br>Carnarvon coat of arms in a context when having a powerful <br>noble’s favor might be useful. Add the Medallion bearing the <br>Carnarvon Coat of Arms and a large sum of money to your <br>equipment.<br>The Challenger (Special Gift for James the <br>Swordsman)<br>Requirement: Face Pietrik or the Lost Boys at least once.<br>The young rioters and their boss remind you of the band</p><p>1<br>2a<br>2b<br>89<br>of cowards who trapped you and are responsible for you <br>losing your hand. Receive 1 Additional Success for every <br>action you take against them if it means you defeat or <br>humiliate them. If you abandon a fight or are forced to <br>retreat, you lose 1 Soma out of shame.<br>The Scenario I Don’t <br>Believe in Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE – The summoning<br>It’s the same one you find on page 82. <br>End of Scene:  After the interview with George, the <br>Hunters can decide whether to collect clues at the <br>Carnarvon villa (SECOND SCENE OPTION A – On <br>Gwendolyn’s trail) or go to the Sirens’ Inn to talk to Basil <br>(SECOND SCENE OPTION B – Basil’s tale).</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710168,"modifiedTime":1781513710168,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UgsxeY5tJTayX2Dh","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Don't Believe - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION A <br>– On Gwendolyn’s trail <br>Read aloud to the Hunters: George takes you through the <br>private rooms of his villa, to Gwendolyn’s room. Waiting for <br>you is the girl’s personal maid, a thirty-year-old woman with <br>typical Eastern European features. The servant introduces <br>herself as Nana, a nickname Gwendolyn had given her. The <br>room of the young Carnarvon girl is the classic room of a <br>young lady, full of books and maps of the world.<br>Place: Gwendolyn Carnarvon’s bedroom.<br>Time: A bit later in the afternoon of a gloomy autumn day.<br>Information: Speaking with Nana, it will be clear to <br>the Hunters that the servant is sincerely concerned about <br>Gwendolyn’s fate; this should dispel any doubts about the <br>servant’s involvement in the disappearance. Nana will tell <br>the Hunters about the frequent night visits that Gwendolyn <br>received, but without being able to put a face or name to <br>her nightly visitor. At the end of the interview, Nana will <br>give the Hunters the poppy petals she found under the bed. <br>From a quick investigation, the Hunters will discover that <br>those flowers are typical of the Kensington Gardens.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters will move towards the gardens <br>to follow the petals’ trail. Go to the THIRD SCENE – The <br>Gardens.</p><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION B – <br>Basil’s Tale<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You easily find the Sirens’ <br>Inn; it is a dive bar in the slums where the poor and drunks <br>belly up at the bar for a cheap beer. You recognize Basil from <br>the leg bandage and the old wooden crutch resting next to <br>his chair. The young man looks drunk, sipping a beer while <br>complaining about the misfortune he had in ending up in the <br>service of Lord Carnarvon.<br>Place: The run-down Sirens’ Inn, full of patrons and poor <br>people.<br>Time: The sun has just set and the large fireplace of the inn <br>casts the patrons’ long shadows on the dirty walls. <br>Information: Talking to Basil, you will get all the <br>information on page 85. During the interview, the <br>Hunters will notice a boy watching them sitting in front of <br>one of the large windows. Once Pietrik understands that</p><p>3<br>4<br>90<br>the Hunters are investigating the Lost Boys, he will launch an <br>assault supported by 8 of his crew. If the fight turns against <br>them, Pietrik and his comrades will escape thanks to the <br>Seals. However, at least one of the Lost Boys will stay behind <br>and can be captured by the Hunters. After the interrogation, <br>the Hunters will ascertain that the gang’s next target is the <br>Skullem Factory. <br>End of Scene:  The Hunters must run to prevent the <br>impending attack on the factory. Go to FOURTH SCENE – <br>The assault on Skullem.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710168,"modifiedTime":1781513710168,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bHVIOIbITF0Nxk4W","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Don't Believe - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE –  The Gardens<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The Kensington Gardens are <br>an architectural and botanical wonder, and even months of <br>abandonment by the gardeners can’t entirely spoil their beauty. <br>Lord Carnarvon got you a key with great ease and you can <br>venture into the park using the main gate. As you step forward, <br>your attention is drawn to a small house in the middle of the <br>park where you clearly see a human figure holding a lantern. <br>It is more than a little suspicious, as no one is supposed to be <br>in the Gardens.<br>Place: The beautiful Kensington Gardens. <br>Time: Night has just fallen.<br>Information: Once at the house, the <br>Hunters will surprise Pietrik as he brings <br>food to Gwendolyn. The young man will <br>try to drive the Hunters out. If it fails, he <br>will flee, flying away (thanks to the power <br>of the Personal Seal Gift). By interrogating Gwendolyn, the <br>Hunters will learn of the attack on the Skullem Factory. <br>End of Scene:  The Hunters must run to prevent the <br>impending attack on the factory. Go to FOURTH SCENE – <br>The assault on Skullem.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710168,"modifiedTime":1781513710168,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"eb3hnzXc9jzCjKgl","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Don't Believe - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE –  The assault <br>on Skullem<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you reach the factory, <br>the first flames are already devouring the building. Among <br>workers and guards on the run, you clearly see a gang of boys <br>throwing strange berries that explode like bombs when they <br>hit the ground. The youngsters’ targets are the two large ovens, <br>which, if blown up, would intensify the flames, engulfing the <br>entire district.<br>Place: The Skullem Factory, besieged by the Lost Boys.<br>Time: It is late at night, but the flames that lick the building <br>illuminate everything as if it were day.<br>Information: Pietrik, with the support of <br>10 Lost Boys, will fight the Hunters. At the <br>end of the clash, several situations may occur.<br> ◆ If Pietrik is captured by the Hunters, he <br>can be persuaded to speak (using Gwendolyn <br>as a lever will be a great strategy); the young <br>man will reveal the location of the Cauldron <br>Fae’s Lair.<br> ◆ If Pietrik escapes, one of the captured <br>Lost Boys will reveal what Pietrik said: the</p><p>5<br>91<br>power of the Seals comes from a sorcerer hiding under <br>Kensington Gardens.<br> ◆ In both cases, the captured gang member will reveal that <br>the goal of the Lost Boys is to destroy what is modern in <br>order to bring peace to London. <br>End of Scene: It will be clear for the Hunters that the one <br>who pulls the strings of the whole story hides under the <br>Kensington Gardens. Go to FIFTH SCENE – The Cauldron <br>Fae.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710168,"modifiedTime":1781513710168,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ixWLSGA2rZSygtDW","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Don't Believe - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE –  The Cauldron <br>Fae<br>This Scene has no precise breakdown because it can be <br>approached in different ways by the Hunters. The Cauldron <br>Fae will be willing to compromise to save Pietrik, or fight to <br>the death if the Hunters prove hostile. Whatever happens, <br>it will be clear that the old fairy cannot accept the change <br>that is slowly transforming her beloved city into a large <br>industrial metropolis.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710168,"modifiedTime":1781513710168,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","collection":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","pages":"81-92"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710168,"modifiedTime":1781513710168,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"kyJkR5oejI5LMjJV","name":"Stegeborg's Quiet","pages":[{"_id":"U6jcPQzanpz3eE3y","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Stegeborg's Quiet</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> The Broken Ones</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 135-150.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/stegeborgs-quiet-p135-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729795,"modifiedTime":1781513729795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"phpPhWIorzPWxGtO","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Setup</h2><p>134<br>Once upon a time…<br>The Hunters are sent to Sweden to <br>investigate the mysterious Stegeborg <br>Castle. The property, once run by the <br>Schwernis family, has been abandoned <br>for decades. The surrounding villages <br>had survived the departure of the noble <br>family, remaining populated and lively. <br>However, in the last few weeks, they <br>have gone ominously silent. Strange <br>lights have been seen coming from <br>the Stegeborg Castle, and seers in the <br>service of the Order have received a dark <br>omen. Something evil, hidden within <br>the meandering corridors of Stegeborg, <br>has been awakened. Now, everyone <br>will pay for the sins of one man. The <br>Hunters must go to Stegeborg and face <br>the danger the seers have foretold.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Sleeping <br>Beauty (Charles Perrault)<br>Stegeborg’s Quiet<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Incest / Physical and Psychological <br>Abuse / Rape / Body Horror</p><p>135<br>The story that led us here…<br>The last member of the Schwernis family, former <br>lords of Stegeborg, remains in the castle. Talia never left  <br>when the castle was abandoned fifty years ago, and instead <br>was bound in eternal slumber. Talia had always submitted <br>to her father Alexander and mother Alexandra, twins <br>united in a perverse relationship. The couple was obsessed <br>with their daughter, who was the last of their children. <br>Each of the previous pregnancies had ended with the birth <br>of deformed children, all of whom had been smothered <br>by their disappointed parents. Talia represented the pure <br>beauty Alexander and Alexandra had been longing for. <br>Their dreams realized, they withdrew within the walls of <br>the castle and hid themselves from the rest of the world. <br>In her stone prison, Talia suffered all kinds of abuse at her <br>parents’ hands, finding support only in Carabosse, the old <br>cook of the castle. Unbeknownst to Talia, Carabosse was <br>once a powerful witch who escaped the great inquisition of <br>1645 in France. When Talia bled for the first time, her father <br>tried to force himself on her. The young woman fought <br>back and, unintentionally, pushed Alexander out of one <br>of the castle towers, causing his death. Crazed with pain, <br>Alexandra tried to kill her daughter, but was stopped by <br>Carabosse. The witch was moved with compassion for all of <br>Talia’s pain, and cast her last and greatest spell: she froze the <br>Stegeborg Castle in time. Talia, asleep in the underground <br>crypt, was imbued with the witch’s power so that she could <br>now move objects or grow plants merely through force of <br>will. Alexandra was transformed into a monster and forced <br>to be her daughter’s guardian for eternity. Talia’s wish <br>covered Stegeborg with ivy and brambles, a symbol of its <br>separation from the rest of the world. <br>The young woman, forever asleep, waits for someone pure <br>of heart and capable of breaking the magic that once saved <br>her, only to deliver her to a life of fading dreams. <br>Fifty years later, Accursio De Celeste, a renowned mercenary <br>and researcher, went to Stegeborg, attracted by rumors of a <br>rich treasure hidden in the castle’s dungeons. Overcoming <br>uncounted dangers, the man reached the dungeons to <br>discover the sleeping body of Talia, who was so impressed by <br>so much courage and skill that she decided to let him come <br>even closer. But Talia’s dreams were once more shattered <br>by the darkness of the human soul. Like her father fifty <br>years earlier, Accursio tried to abuse the beautiful Sleeper. <br>Anger and resentment once again overcame Talia’s mind, <br>animating the castle and cursing the entire village next to it. <br>In one night, all the inhabitants were killed or assimilated <br>by the castle, becoming monsters and prisoners. Accursio <br>took refuge in the Master Tower, waiting for his chance to <br>escape. Her soul forever scarred, Talia’s will is now out of <br>control, expanding beyond the walls of Stegeborg, in a slow <br>but inexorable attempt to assimilate the whole world.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>The village near the castle is nothing more than a ghost town <br>where Georg, the only survivor of Talia’s fury, takes refuge <br>from the Quiet Guards: men and women merged with the <br>furnishings of the castle and transfigured into monsters, <br>now serving the Sleeper. Accursio lives in the Master Tower <br>of the castle where Talia’s power struggles to reach since <br>it is there that Alexander tried to rape his daughter. The <br>memory of so much pain weakens her abilities. Accursio <br>is aware that he cannot escape on his own, since the tower <br>has a single exit to the inner courtyard of the castle, and <br>Talia’s power can reach him there. Alexandra, now reduced</p><p>1<br>STEGEBORG<br>136<br>to a deformed monster, wanders through the castle and waits <br>for someone to end her life. She had trusted Accursio, and <br>now that the man has proven as despicable as Alexander, <br>Alexandra has resigned herself to the idea that no one can <br>ever give Talia peace and thus put an end to the curse. A few <br>villagers led by a woman named Lisbet are kept alive inside <br>the castle, in the rooms that once belonged to the Schwernis <br>family. Talia holds them hostage, forcing them every night to <br>keep her company by reading stories and singing songs.</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729796,"modifiedTime":1781513729796,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"c9NmZQO1UhCUftDa","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  It is almost sunset when you <br>glimpse the first houses of the village of Stegeborg. The imposing <br>shape of the castle looms over the small village, casting its great <br>shadow as if to swallow it. While an old stray dog raises its ears <br>in your direction, the unnatural silence that accompanies your <br>footsteps does not bode well.<br>Place: The small village of Stegeborg, devastated by the fury <br>of Talia.<br>Time: It is almost sunset, but the sky is clear and there is still <br>plenty of light.<br>Initial Situation: It’s apparent the village has suffered some <br>sort of disaster as soon as the Hunters arrive there. Doors <br>and windows are literally crumbling, while dozens of corpses <br>lie in the streets. On the wrists and neck of the bodies, one <br>can see the clear marks of something that seized them tightly <br>and dragged them with incredible force. Moving around the <br>village will immediately attract the attention of the Quiet <br>Guards, who will converge on the Hunters. There are a total of <br>10 Guards in town. Georg took refuge in the church, but the <br>fear of being captured led him to stay there for days and he <br>almost died of hunger. <br>Information: Saving Georg will yield some information. <br>The man arrived in Stegeborg a few years ago and does not <br>know the history of the Schwernis well. He does know that <br>fifty years earlier something so upset the noble family they <br>packed up and left in a single night, disappearing. Georg will <br>also reveal that, a week ago, an Italian treasure hunter named <br>Accursio De Celeste passed through the village, asking for <br>information about the castle. That same evening, he went <br>there, never to return. Soon after, all hell broke loose, and the <br>plants in the village came to life, dragging and strangling its <br>inhabitants. Georg survived by fleeing to the church. He hid <br>there, afraid to move after witnessing several villagers being <br>transformed into Quiet Guards.<br>Important note: Thanks to her Sleeping Spirit Gift, Talia <br>can interact with all the Places in the Scenario. Depending <br>on the actions of the Hunters, the Sleeper can be an ally or an <br>enemy. On page 142, you can find instructions for managing <br>the Sleeping Spirit Gift.</p><p>STEGEBORG<br>137<br>The Village of <br>Stegeborg<br>Descriptor: A small village at the foot of Castle Stegeborg, <br>devastated by the fury of Talia.<br>Georg the Survivor <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was <br>living in the streets.<br>Agenda: Escape from Stegeborg as soon as possible, so I can <br>leave what I saw behind me and start a new life.<br>The Quiet Guards <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused <br>with some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations <br>have driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of <br>Talia.<br>Gift – Quiet Guards:  A Quiet Guard no longer possesses <br>a mind and acts as an object under the control of Talia. That <br>is why they cannot be mentally manipulated or frightened <br>in any way. Each Quiet Guard is a human body fused with a <br>part of the castle. Roll a die or choose a mutation.<br>1. Tools: The Guard’s arms are an agglomeration of tools, <br>such as shears and hammers. When attacking, the Guard is <br>considered to have an OL Medium 5.<br>2. Grating: The Guard’s body is covered with metal grates <br>and frames. It can suffer 1 additional Wound.<br>3. Chains: Ropes and chains hang from the Guard’s body. <br>With a single action, the Guard can interact with 2 targets.<br>4. Door: The Guard’s body is a huge pile of metal doors <br>and hinges. When defending itself, the Guard is considered <br>to have an OL Medium.<br>5. Fireplace: Burning embers are kept ablaze within the <br>Guard’s stomach. Once per Scene, the Guard’s attack inflicts <br>1 additional Wound.<br>6. Plates:  The Guard’s body is a cluster of plates and <br>glasses embedded in the living skin. When the Guard is <br>eliminated, it explodes into a thousand shards, inflicting <br>1 Wound to the one who dealt the last blow unless they <br>succeed a Defense Check.</p><p>138<br>The Castle’s Courtyard<br>Descriptor: A large inner courtyard, which was once a <br>lavish garden. Now, ivy and brambles infest every crevice, <br>forming a real forest.<br>Threat – Forest of Animated <br>Brambles<br>Descriptor: Brambles and ivy animated by Talia’s ability. <br>We act to capture and strangle any intruders. We are guarding <br>the courtyard, waiting to end Accursio’s life.<br>OL Hard 7<br>Gift – Forest of Brambles:  The mass of brambles acts <br>under the magical power of Talia and can perform 1d6 <br>actions per Exchange. Each individual action can be used <br>in a different way. 1. Attacking:  Whip at or strangle a <br>target and inflict 1 Wound; 2. Ensnaring:  Immobilize <br>a target, preventing it from acting; 3. Manipulating: <br>Manipulate objects or the setting to open or close passages;  <br>4. Communicating:  Take the shape of rudimentary <br>letters. The Forest cannot be destroyed unless it is <br>completely set on fire and, even then, it will regenerate <br>within a few minutes. By inflicting 1 Wound, it’s possible <br>to hack away some branches and slow down the plants’ <br>growth, for example, to free an ensnared target. If Accursio <br>is present the Forest of Animated Brambles will focus on <br>capturing him, devoting at least half its actions to that <br>purpose.<br>Information: Access to the courtyard is easy, as the large <br>drawbridge of the castle is lowered. From the Courtyard, <br>you can access the Master Tower and the Main Court.<br>The Master Tower<br>Descriptor: A large six-story fortified tower, with barred <br>windows. The large main door is walled by brambles and <br>plants.<br>Information: Talia has blocked the only exit with her <br>Forest of Animated Brambles and attempting to force it will <br>activate its Threat (see previous column). By inflicting a <br>total of 3 Wounds to the brambles, you can open the door. <br>Accursio has taken refuge on the third floor where, slowly, <br>he is sawing the bars out of a window with the intention <br>of stretching a rope to the walls and escaping. Accursio <br>is the only one, besides Alexandra, who has a key to the <br>Dungeons.<br>Accursio De Celeste <br>Mercenary and Researcher of Renowned Fame<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, <br>and I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what <br>I want. <br>Agenda: Escape from Stegeborg while keeping the secret of <br>what I have done, as well as keeping the treasure I have found <br>/ Take advantage of the arrival of the Hunters in Stegeborg to <br>appease the fury of Talia. <br>Gift – Good at Escaping:  Accursio is skilled at making <br>himself scarce when things get bad. Increase his OL by 1 <br>for all actions involving fleeing or avoiding a menace. Once <br>per Scene, Accursio can move away from a place without <br>anyone being able to stop or see him. To do this, however, <br>it is necessary that something happens that can attract the</p><p>Master<br>Tower<br>Arrival<br>DrawbridgeCourtyardEntry Hall<br>Formal Dining <br>Room<br>Kitchens<br>Fireplace<br>&lt; Pantry<br>&lt; Staircase to cellars<br>&lt; Upwards stairsServants’ ChambersServants’ Chambers<br>Connection CorridorConnection Corridor<br>Guard RoomGuard Room<br>139<br>general attention for a few moments, such as a fight or a <br>sudden event.<br>Main Court <br>Descriptor: The largest block of rooms and halls of the castle. <br>Despite the passing of time, it’s still possible <br>to see faded hints of past splendors and <br>beauty.<br>Information: The Hunters enter <br>the castle by its entry hall, a <br>large room with several pieces of furniture on which visitors <br>could leave coats and weapons. From the entry hall, you can <br>access the Formal Dining Room and the Servant’s Chambers. <br>Use the map of Stegeborg to see what the Hunters are up <br>against. Some rooms on the map do not have pre-established <br>encounters. As with Events, feel free to create content in <br>accordance with the Hunters’ choices.<br>First <br>floor</p><p>Noble Rooms<br>Tapestry Room<br>Balcony Balcony &lt; Balcony<br>&lt; Balcony<br>Fireplace<br>Guard Room<br>&lt;<br>Staircase to <br>first floor<br>140<br>Formal Dining Room<br>A large and lavish ballroom where there are 6 Quiet Guards.<br>Kitchens<br>The great kitchens of the castle. By crawling up inside the fireplace’s <br>chimney, you can reach the Noble Rooms on the second floor. By <br>inspecting the Kitchens, you can see that meals are still being prepared. <br>From the Kitchens, one can access the Cellars (page 141).<br>Servants’ Chambers<br>Upon entering the Servant’s Quarters, the Hunters will find the bodies <br>of servants half melded with walls and sinking into the floor, frozen in <br>expressions of terror. Getting too close to the walls will rouse the servants, <br>animating them.<br>Connection Corridor<br>A large corridor in the east wing of the castle. From the large, barred <br>windows, the Hunters will notice the figure of a man moving in the <br>Master Tower. It is Accursio, working hard on his escape.<br>Threat – Walls of Memory<br>Descriptor: Bodies and stone come alive to hold intruders in <br>a crazy embrace.<br>OL Easy 3<br>Gift – The Horror Sculpted in the Stone:  When the <br>Walls of Memory come alive, surprised targets receive 1 <br>Penalty to any potential Defense Check. The walls grab a <br>target and whisper words of despair and suffering in their <br>ears. Those who hear them must decide whether to lose 1 <br>Soma or suffer 1 Wound before freeing themselves.<br>Second <br>floor</p><p>141<br>The Guard Room<br>A narrow, small chamber tucked between the two floors <br>of the castle, divided into two by a wooden weapon rack. <br>A large, barred door leads to the Noble Rooms. Trying <br>to open the door without Talia’s permission activates the <br>Phantom Weapons Threat, which will attack the intruders <br>as long as they remain in the room.<br>Threat – Phantom Weapons<br>Descriptor: A series of weapons that float in the air, ready <br>to strike at unwelcome visitors.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Gift – Blade Storm:  When this Threat is activated, 1d6 <br>different targets will be attacked by a blade during each <br>Exchange. If there are more attacking blades than targets, <br>each target receives 1 Penalty to Defense Checks to avoid <br>being hit. Two additional attacking blades impose 2 <br>Penalties to Defense Checks to all targets, and so forth.<br>The Tapestry Room<br>A large and sumptuous room covered with tapestries and <br>paintings depicting the Schwernis family. Almost all the <br>paintings are untouched, but the largest on the north wall <br>is ruined. It’s possible to make out that the painting depicts <br>a family: father, mother, and daughter. The parents are <br>so similar that they look like twins. The husband’s face is <br>obscured by old blood, while the mother’s body has been <br>warped by cuts and stains making it look like a monster. <br>The daughter, a cold and sad figure in the pose, has two <br>scratches on her eyes, making them appear closed.<br>Cellars<br>In the large Cellars of the castle, the old barrels and piles of <br>dirt are home to Alexandra. The monster will not hesitate <br>to attack any intruder. Here a large metal hatch allows <br>access to the Dungeons of the castle. The hatch is locked <br>with Talia’s magic, but it can be opened with her key. There <br>are two copies. One is in the possession of Alexandra and <br>the other is held by Accursio.<br>Alexandra the Mother<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (5 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. <br>The curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget <br>what I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can <br>only grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the <br>forgiveness of my daughter.<br>Agenda: After more than fifty years of a cursed existence, <br>I have come to understand the damage my sins have done. <br>Unable to beg for her forgiveness, I show my daughter how <br>much I regret the past by doing anything she asks of me.<br>Gift – Deformed Orc:  Alexandra is a huge monster with <br>herculean strength. She can act twice during an Exchange, <br>but not consecutively. The curse makes Alexandra resistant <br>to magic. Any action using magic that involves her receives <br>1 Penalty.<br>Information: Upon her death, Alexandra’s body <br>will reverse to that of a gorgeous middle-aged woman. <br>Alexandra is the only one, besides Accursio, who has a key <br>to the Dungeons.</p><p>Talia<br>Talia<br>142<br>Noble Rooms<br>Descriptor: A series of rich and beautiful rooms, preserved <br>despite the years passed.<br>Information: The only survivors of the village are held <br>prisoner in this part of the castle. Talia has Alexandra pick up <br>Lisbet every night to take her to the Dungeons and read her a <br>story. Lisbet is a young mother and her two children, Marita <br>and Lars, are among the prisoners. Lisbet realized that Talia <br>is nothing but a wounded spirit, so she tries to comfort the <br>girl by slowly gaining her trust. Lisbet’s hope is that sooner or <br>later, Talia will release her and all the other prisoners.<br>Lisbet<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a young widow and I settled in the village <br>to start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, <br>which have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. <br>However, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.<br>Agenda: To save all the prisoners by convincing Talia to do <br>the right thing. <br>The Dungeons<br>Descriptor: A series of tunnels and galleries full of barred <br>doors leading to the treasure room.<br>Talia the Sleeper <br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the <br>magic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, <br>thanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.<br>Agenda: Revenge myself on Accursio, who betrayed my trust <br>the way so many others have / Finding peace through death, or <br>assimilating everything I can with my power.<br>Gift – Sleeping Spirit:  Talia can literally manipulate the <br>entire castle as she pleases. During each Exchange, she can <br>perform up to 3 of the following actions. 1. Manipulate: <br>Move or reshape an object of the castle into something else; <br>2. Attack:  Throw and move objects to inflict 1 Wound;  <br>3. Reject:  Prevent people from moving, entering, or <br>leaving by manipulating objects, or even the castle itself. <br>Talia cannot speak, but she can use Manipulate to write or <br>compose rudimentary messages through objects. Talia can <br>concentrate all 3 actions into one with devastating effects. It <br>can collapse an entire wing of the castle or open a deep well <br>in the ground. The effects of this action are wide-ranging and, <br>at the discretion of the Storyteller, may remove one or more <br>Hunters who fail a Defense Check from the Scene.<br>Information: Next to Talia’s sleeping body, one can find her <br>diary, written with a pen manipulated by her hair. It tells the <br>Sleeper’s whole sad story.</p><p>143<br>Note: Talia’s Gift, Sleeping Spirit, can be used in <br>countless ways throughout the Scenario. Below is a <br>set of suggestions for the Storyteller. Extracts of Talia’s <br>diary are on page 148.<br>Talia can:<br> ◆ Leave messages on pictures and furniture or send <br>the Hunters a page from her diary.<br> ◆ Lock and open doors to provide guidance.<br> ◆ Move the curtains on the windows to illuminate a <br>dark room.<br> ◆ Distort the paintings in the Tapestry Room so <br>her tragedy is better understood.<br> ◆ Lock the drawbridge to prevent someone from <br>escaping.<br> ◆ Withdraw the brambles from outside the castle, <br>pulling them in through the windows.<br> ◆ Use one of the prisoners as a warning.<br> ◆ Draw the Hunters’ attention to one of Accurio’s <br>belongings that has been left in the castle, and <br>which can hint at his presence.<br> ◆ Open a well in the treasure room as a way of warning <br>the Hunters away.</p><p>144<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel free <br>to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunters.<br>At dawn on the day following the arrival of the <br>Hunters: Accursio will finish sawing the bars and will try to <br>escape by descending from the walls. Talia will unleash her <br>abilities and will capture him, taking him to the dungeons to <br>punish him.<br>If the Hunters manage to rescue Accursio from <br>Stegeborg: Talia will give into her fury, killing all the <br>prisoners except Lisbet. Now, the new target of the Sleeper’s <br>hatred will be the Hunters.<br>If the Hunters show interest in the history of the <br>Schwernis family:  Talia will ease the pressure on the <br>intruders, trying to guide them to the Tapestry Room.<br>If the Hunters make it clear to Lisbet that they are <br>there to save her:  the woman will say that she has read <br>some pages of Talia’s diary and that the spirit acts only out of <br>pain and trauma.<br>If the Hunters find a way to communicate with <br>Alexandra: she will ask them to save Talia from herself by <br>helping her to feel hope once more. Then she will drive the <br>Hunters to kill her by attacking them, so she can finally be <br>free from the curse.<br>If the Hunters reveal themselves to Accursio: he will <br>tell them that a spirit roams in the castle and that perhaps <br>something the adventurer stole has enraged it. The scoundrel <br>will seem sincerely repentant and will deliver what he has <br>stolen to the Hunters so that they can bring it back to the <br>basement and “appease” the spirit.<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the Stegeborg’s <br>Quiet Scenario and can be acquired once the requirements <br>are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario Gift and if they <br>acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the previous one.<br>Adept of the Quiet<br>Requirement: To have witnessed a manifestation of Talia’s <br>abilities within the castle.<br>Y ou realize that having a calm spirit prevents the castle from <br>perceiving you as a threat. Receive 1 Additional Success in <br>all Defense Checks you make against a manifestation of the <br>power of Stegeborg or a creature associated with the powers <br>of spirits.<br>The Castle’s Secrets<br>Requirement: Learn the secret passages of the castle from <br>Accursio or Lisbet.<br>Y ou know some of the many secret passages that connect the <br>whole castle. During a Scene, you can spend 1 Soma to find <br>a passage from one place to another in the castle, as long as <br>you have been there before. Y ou can’t leave the castle walls <br>with this Gift.</p><p>3a<br>1<br>2<br>145</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  Arrival at the <br>Village<br>It’s the same one you find on page 136.<br>End of Scene: After learning from Georg what happened <br>to the village and Accursio’s disappearance, the Hunters <br>continue their investigation at the castle. Go to the SECOND <br>SCENE – The Castle’s Courtyard.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"k74pwhIuE9sJoFZo","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE – The Castle’s <br>Courtyard<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  After crossing the large <br>drawbridge, you finally arrive at the castle’s immense garden. <br>Brambles and ivy cover everything, and Georg’s description of <br>the havoc the plants caused in the village sounds more like <br>a story made up to frighten children. Two lights attract your <br>attention. One comes from the third floor of the large Master <br>Tower to your left. The second light shines from the second <br>floor of the castle. All the windows have thick bars and you <br>soon understand that the entrance doors of the two structures <br>are the only way to access the buildings.<br>Location: The large inner garden of the castle.<br>Time: Night has now fallen, a light coming from the tower <br>and one from the second floor of the castle shine in the dark.<br>Information: Talia will follow the actions of the Hunters <br>to understand their intentions and then animate the castle to <br>close them in by raising <br>the drawbridge. See <br>the Animated Bramble <br>Forest Threat on page <br>138.<br>End of Scene:  To <br>escape from the animated <br>brambles, the Hunters can <br>decide to enter the tower, <br>go to THIRD SCENE <br>OPTION A – Master Tower, <br>or the castle, go to THIRD SCENE OPTION B – Main Court.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LrTT3680eaZHSi3F","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>Master Tower<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you eventually enter <br>the tower, the brambles seem to recoil as if frightened of the <br>place. A call for help comes from the stairs. It seems whoever <br>inhabits the third floor has witnessed your escape and is <br>descending at a rapid pace towards you.<br>Place: The old Master Tower, where Talia killed her father <br>to defend herself fifty years earlier.<br>Time: It is night and only Accursio’s lantern’s light <br>illuminates the bare, gray rooms of the tower.<br>Information: Accursio will ask the Hunters for help, but <br>he will soon understand that they too can do little against <br>the power of Talia. The cunning adventurer will tell the <br>Hunters that an evil spirit resides in the castle and that, <br>The Scenario Stegeborg’s <br>Quiet in Scenes</p><p>3b<br>4<br>146<br>in his search of treasures, he must have inadvertently <br>awakened it. Appearing repentant, Accursio will ask the <br>Hunters to do something to save him since they are here <br>to solve the mystery. However, he will refuse to leave the <br>Tower, pointing out that the thorns almost killed him <br>when he tried to escape. To help the Hunters, Accursio will <br>show them one of the secret passages leading directly to <br>the Noble Rooms on the second floor. He will explain to <br>the Hunters that from there you can descend into a large <br>fireplace, reach the Kitchens, and then descend into the <br>Cellars where the evil spirit is located, avoiding most of the <br>dangers of the castle. <br>End of Scene:  Following Accursio’s directions, the <br>Hunters enter the castle through a secret passage, go to the</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7D8I6quQmv9Cp7LX","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE – Noble Rooms.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LrTT3680eaZHSi3F","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  <br>Main Court<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you finally enter the <br>castle, the brambles seem to settle and still once more as if <br>nothing had happened. In front of you is the huge castle of <br>Stegeborg, a maze with over one hundred rooms.<br>Place: The gloomy and abandoned castle of Stegeborg.<br>Time: It is night and only the light brought by the Hunters <br>illuminates the large dust-covered rooms.<br>Information: When exploring the castle, the Hunters <br>will pass through various Places (presented on page 139) <br>in the following order:<br>Servants’ Chambers (page 140)<br>Tapestry Room (page 141)<br>Guard Room (page 141)<br>Talia will observe the Hunters and can intervene thanks to <br>her Sleeping Spirit Gift (page 142).<br>End of Scene:  Past the Guard Room, the Hunters will <br>have access to the second floor, go to the FOURTH SCENE <br>– Noble Rooms.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7D8I6quQmv9Cp7LX","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE – Noble Rooms<br>Note: The Hunters can reach this Scene after exploring the <br>castle or thanks to the secret passage indicated by Accursio. <br>In the second case, before setting up this Scene, they will <br>go through the Tapestry Room (page 141) and then the <br>Guard Room (page 141).<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You close the big door behind <br>you and you can hear the clang of the ghostly weapons that <br>still slam on the heavy wrought iron reinforcements. This <br>area of the castle seems illuminated and in fact, within a few <br>moments, some human figures stare at you from the bottom <br>of a large dining room. A woman with a thin and tired face <br>raises a hand in greeting.<br>Place: The castle’s main room, where the Schwernis family <br>lived.<br>Time: It is past midnight.<br>Information: Lisbet will welcome the Hunters, telling <br>them that all the prisoners are kept alive by a monster that <br>lives in the cellars, which regularly brings food and water. <br>Lisbet is often taken to the castle’s basement by the creature <br>to read or sing old stories to a girl who seems frozen in <br>perpetual sleep. Talking to Lisbet, the Hunters will also <br>discover:<br> ◆ The monstrous creature that feeds the prisoners moves <br>freely around the castle and possesses incredible <br>strength.</p><p>5<br>6<br>147<br> ◆ From the large fireplace in the dining room, you can <br>go downstairs to the Kitchens. From there you can <br>reach the Cellars where you can find the hatch for the <br>Dungeons. If the Hunters have spoken to Accursio, <br>they will then have confirmation that the man was not <br>lying.<br> ◆ Lisbet will say that the sleeping girl seems unutterably <br>sad and, despite what she has done in the village, Lisbet <br>cannot help but feel compassion for her rather than <br>hatred.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can wait until Alexandra arrives <br>to ambush her or climb down the chimney and face her <br>directly in the Cellars. Go to THE FIFTH SCENE – The <br>Castle’s Orc.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"uvtk4oRAfYNp0qYz","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE – The Castle’s Orc<br>Note: This Scene kicks off when the Hunters face <br>Alexandra.<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  What stands before your <br>eyes is a grotesque creature with vaguely human features. <br>An old noble woman’s dress dangles from its shape like a rag, <br>soiled with blood and ichor. The being is short of breath, but <br>its muscles are tense and powerful. Only the eyes glow with <br>a deep light of suffering and madness, protruding from the <br>deformed face, which is dotted with pustules and bubbles. <br>The being roars with all its anger before hurling itself against <br>you.<br>Place: The castle cellars or the dining room where all the <br>prisoners are kept.<br>Time: A few hours left until dawn.<br>Information: Alexandra will fight to the death, in the <br>hope that the Hunters will end her life, freeing her from the <br>curse. Once she’s killed, she’ll turn back into the beautiful <br>woman she once was. Around her neck, she wears a chain <br>with the key to the Dungeons’ trapdoor.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can descend into the Dungeons <br>and finally meet Talia. Go to SCENE SIX – The Sad Sleeper.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0X5Z0N46JvWjXyrZ","name":"Scene 6","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 6</h2><p>SIXTH SCENE –  The Sad <br>Sleeper<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You pass down a few <br>long corridors before arriving at the castle’s large treasure <br>room. The door is wide open, and an unnatural green light <br>illuminates the entire room. The strange glow radiates from <br>a young girl floating in the air, asleep in an unnatural torpor. <br>Her skin is as cold and pale as that of a corpse. Only the very <br>long blond hair that lashes and moves unsettlingly allows you <br>to understand that this being is alive.<br>Place: The treasure room of the castle.<br>Time: The sun begins to rise as Accursio attempts his great <br>escape.<br>Information: Talia’s reaction will vary depending on <br>what the Hunters have done so far. Shortly after the Hunters <br>arrive, Accursio will be carried into the room by a group of <br>Quiet Guards and dragged in front of Talia to be executed.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters will be key to tipping the scales <br>in the epilogue of the sad story of the Sleeper of Stegeborg.</p><p>148<br>Talia’s <br>diary<br>Page 1 <br>How long will this captivity last? My parents say it is <br>for my own good, but in the meantime, sixteen years of <br>my life have passed without me ever setting foot outside <br>these walls. Father finally quieted my complaints by <br>giving me the keys to the Master Tower. I love spending <br>hours and hours in the tower, studying the villagers. <br>They go about their daily tasks, never knowing that I <br>sit here in a gilded cage and watch, longing to join in <br>their normal lives.<br>Page 2<br>My mother got very angry with the cook. Apparently, <br>she’s not as good a cook as Mother thought. The <br>problem is, Mother can be quite unreasonable. More <br>than once, I have seen her take out a fit of bad temper <br>on the servants. My father does nothing to stop her. On <br>the contrary, he seems to enjoy watching my mother <br>mercilessly wielding her authority to misuse the <br>servants. In the end, the cook ran away, leaving the <br>castle. My mother started calling her terrible names, <br>saying that such terrible food would have shamed <br>the whole Schwernis family. At dinner, my father <br>whispered something in my mother’s ear, running his <br>finger down her throat, and then together they laughed <br>rudely. I felt a shiver down my spine.<br>If I were a magician I would turn my mother into a <br>monster, because that’s what she is. Even if she looks <br>like a noblewoman, her soul is black and overflowing <br>with evil.<br>Page 3<br>The new cook is called Carabosse. She is a foreigner. <br>With the rumors about Mother’s cruelty, I don’t <br>wonder why no one in the village wants to work at the <br>castle anymore. Carabosse has a sweet face like that of <br>a loving grandmother, but also deep green eyes, which <br>seem to shine. She says she hails from the east and, if <br>I remember correctly, the prelate of the village on his <br>last visit spoke to my father of many witches fleeing <br>from the numerous stakes that are in use in Eastern <br>Europe. If Carabosse really is a witch, I hope she uses <br>magic and turns me into a bird. It would be nice to be <br>able to fly beyond these walls, above the clouds.</p><p>149<br>Page 4<br>Mother caught me. Some servant must have tattled on <br>my little visits to the village at night. Or maybe it was <br>the villagers who betrayed me, despite all the coins I <br>gave them... They too are just bloody selfish. Now, every <br>single window in the castle has a thick metal grate, and <br>the transformation from a palace to prison is complete. <br>My parents say this is for my own good, that the world <br>outside the castle is dangerous for a pure soul like mine. <br>That I am the daughter they have always desired, their <br>most precious treasure. But their intentions stifle my <br>soul, drowning it in utter darkness. Only Carabosse <br>understands me, but she seems to grow more and <br>more tired and sick. My father often stares at me with <br>frightening eyes, whispering the word “desired. ” <br>Page 5<br>I’ve discovered the truth and it ruined me. My father <br>and mother are twin siblings. Their love has never been <br>blessed by God and their obsession with a daughter has <br>led them to so many miscarriages. What remains of my <br>brothers and sisters is in the basement, too deformed <br>to survive. When my mother learned what I had <br>discovered, I was sure she would kill me. Instead, she <br>smiled, a sweet smile like I have never seen on her face <br>before. She said I am ready, that I am old enough to run <br>the family. I have been living in this room for a week <br>now, but tomorrow my father will return and a strange <br>feeling grips my heart. I am afraid because no one is <br>coming to save me.<br>Page 6<br>It happened. Mom is devastated by grief, but I don’t <br>regret what I did. When my father tried to… I can’t even <br>write it down. I fought back with all my might. I pushed <br>him away from me, but I didn’t mean for him to fall <br>down the tower. But even though I didn’t intend it, I felt <br>relieved. And at that very moment, I realized that my <br>soul had been forfeited. Now I’m waiting for my mother <br>to decide my fate. She howled in sorrow for the three <br>nights after Father’s fall, cursing God and promising me <br>infinite suffering as punishment for taking away the love <br>of her life.<br>Today, Carabosse came to bring me dinner, gave me a <br>caress on the head, and told me that all this will end. <br>“Sleep, my little one”... were her last words. And with <br>that one kind gesture, I let myself go to sleep. The only <br>real means at my disposal was to escape the walls of <br>Stegeborg.</p>"},"sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","collection":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","pages":"135-150"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xPu3Rk8n4bNgNVzt","name":"Bloodwhite's Heart","pages":[{"_id":"mEc3VdGX2XPiUpd5","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Bloodwhite's Heart</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> The Broken Ones</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 109-122.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/bloodwhites-heart-p109-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717904,"modifiedTime":1781513717904,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5Sek8U8NUOv5Ntsa","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Bloodwhite's Heart - Setup</h2><p>108<br>Once upon a time…<br>Germanic Bavaria. Prince Charles <br>Theodore has summoned the Order after <br>the strange death of his nephew Ottone. <br>He died traveling to the small village of <br>Lohr where he had gone to meet his future <br>wife, Bianca Karenmann. Although official <br>reports speak of a fatal fall from the horse, <br>in truth, the young man’s corpse was found <br>torn apart, his lungs and other organs <br>crushed as if a bomb had exploded within <br>his body. Despite the condolences of Karl <br>and Elsa Karenmann, Prince Charles wants <br>to shed light on his nephew’s death, with the <br>hope that doing so would dispel any shadow <br>of witchcraft and dark rituals. After all, <br>such suspicions had seen Lohr play host to a <br>relentless witch-hunt once before.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Snow <br>White (Grimm Brothers)<br>Bloodwhite’s Heart<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Gore / Body Horror / False Accusations</p><p>109<br>The story that led us here…<br>During the witch hunt that shook the quiet village <br>of Lohr in 1603, a capable and powerful witch named Ursa <br>Radh managed to escape the clutches of the inquisition <br>for fifteen years, until 1618, when the hunt, unfortunately, <br>ended with her capture. While burning at the stake in <br>the village’s public square, Ursa cursed the lineage of the <br>Karenmanns, invoking the curse of the Restless Blood. <br>Karl’s then great-grandfather decided to walk away from <br>Lohr, hoping he would escape the curse, and he did. <br>Later on, his grandson Karl returned to Lohr, tempted by <br>promises of a good political career in the service of Prince <br>Charles Theodore. But his return to Lohr awakened Ursa’s <br>resentful spirit and the curse struck the Karenmann family. <br>Its victim was Bianca, Karl and Elsa’s firstborn daughter. <br>From an early age, she could only be satisfied with raw and <br>bloody meat. The Karenmanns kept their daughter safe <br>from prying eyes, but when Bianca grew old enough, Karl <br>couldn’t help but offer her hand in marriage to Ottone, the <br>Prince’s nephew. Arriving in Lohr, the greedy and spoiled <br>Ottone tried to consummate a relationship with naive <br>Bianca, who unintentionally made him explode to defend <br>herself, thus discovering another of the powers derived <br>from the curse. Panicked, the Karenmann spouses asked <br>Svenn, a skilled huntsman and longtime friend, for help, <br>asking him to secure the young Bianca. The man took <br>Bianca to an old mine where a group of seven Hessian <br>deserters had settled, each of whom had been on the run <br>for years because of war crimes. The seven of them, all <br>suffering from dwarfism, have accepted Bianca into their <br>ranks, swearing to keep her safe, provided the Karenmann <br>family does the same with them.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Karl and Elsa live in fear that the Prince may send others <br>to investigate and, in particular, the Karenmann couple <br>know about the Order and its agents who once took part <br>in the witch hunt that once befell Lohr. That is why they <br>have commissioned Svenn to prepare a trap to mislead any <br>potential investigation. Svenn targeted Bruna, an old widow <br>who lives apart from the village because many rumors point <br>to her being a witch. Svenn hid a book of witchcraft and a <br>lock of hair recovered from Ottone’s body in Bruna’s house <br>so that any investigation would lead to accusing the woman <br>of witchcraft, diverting attention from Bianca. Regarding <br>the Karenmanns’ offspring, it was announced that she left  <br>for Dresden, to enter a prestigious university. In fact, Bianca <br>lives hidden in the old mine half a day from the village, kept <br>safe by Hessian mercenaries. Bianca and the mercenaries <br>have formed a friendly relationship and the young woman <br>spends her time caring for the soldiers and preparing their <br>meals. Abel, a young man from the village who has always <br>been in love with Bianca, did not believe that the young <br>Karenmann moved to Dresden to study. Her parents’ love <br>and attachment to their daughter are well known and <br>they would never have sent her away so easily. Abel has <br>repeatedly tried to understand the mystery behind Bianca’s <br>disappearance, clashing with the indifference of the village <br>and Svenn’s veiled threats.</p><p>1<br>110</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717905,"modifiedTime":1781513717905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qkjEctaByF4Bj0ju","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Bloodwhite's Heart - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You arrive at the small village <br>of Lohr early in the morning, while most of the inhabitants are <br>busy with the many daily chores. Were it not for the macabre <br>discovery of the body of the young Ottone, Lohr would be the <br>portrait of a happy and carefree village. In front of you, right in <br>the center of the village, the Karenmann family palace stands <br>out in all its splendor.<br>Place: The village of Lohr.<br>Time: The early morning of a beautiful, sunny day.<br>Initial Situation: The Hunters are led to a meeting with <br>Karl and Elsa Karenmann.<br>Information: The Karenmann spouses will welcome the <br>Hunters with open arms, trying to appear as cooperative <br>as possible. From the interview, you can have the following <br>information, much of which is tainted by Karl and Elsa to <br>mislead any investigation.<br> ◆ The body of poor Ottone has already been returned to the <br>Prince’s messengers so that he could be taken to his family <br>to receive the funeral he deserves.<br> ◆ Ottone was found in his room, and it appears that he died <br>during the night. The body was in a gruesome condition.<br> ◆ The Karenmanns have hired Svenn, a skilled huntsman <br>and trusted person who has always provided for the <br>village. Svenn’s house is located a few minutes from the <br>Karenmann palace and the man is waiting for the Hunters <br>to share with them what he has discovered during the last <br>week of investigation.<br> ◆ The Karenmanns will carefully avoid mentioning Bianca. <br>If asked about her, they will say that their daughter has <br>moved to Dresden, eager to forget what happened and to <br>devote herself to her studies.<br>Karl and Elsa Karenmann <br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are two loving parents who only want what’s <br>best for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout <br>Lohr.<br>Agenda: To have Ottone’s death case closed as soon as possible, <br>placing the blame on Bruna / Protect Bianca from a world that <br>could not accept her for what she is.<br>Karenmann Palace<br>Descriptor: A large and magnificent palace that contrasts <br>with the humble appearance of the rest of Lohr’s dwellings.<br>During the interview, the Hunters will realize that the palace <br>is full of paintings depicting the Karenmann family. In many <br>paintings, a beautiful girl with long black hair, snow-white <br>skin, and a pure and innocent look can be seen. From the <br>paintings the great love that unites Elsa and Karl to their <br>daughter Bianca is clear.<br>The Village of Lohr<br>Descriptor: A small village that is experiencing new prosperity <br>thanks to the Karenmann family.<br>The Hunters may hear some rumors while exploring the <br>village. Choose or roll 1 die:</p><p>111<br>1. Ottone quickly showed himself to be a stuck-up, <br>arrogant nobleman. Many are happy that sweet <br>Bianca Karenmann no longer has to marry him.<br>2. In the past, Lohr has been at the center of the largest <br>witch hunt in all of Germany. Several stakes were left <br>in the town square as a warning to all inhabitants.<br>3. The Karenmann family administers the village with <br>care and justice. Father, mother, and daughter have <br>always been inseparable.<br>4. Old Bruna is not well-liked, ever since her husband <br>got sick and then died within a week of a strange <br>illness. Many people think that it <br>was Bruna herself who performed <br>witchcraft on her husband, to <br>punish him for being a drunk.<br>5. In years past, the large mine, <br>located just over half a day’s <br>walk away, provided jobs to <br>the villagers. Since it played <br>out, the mine has become <br>a dangerous place where <br>fugitives and deserters often <br>find shelter for the night.<br>6. Bianca is a girl of rare <br>beauty, sweet and kind to <br>everyone. She has become <br>famous in the village for her <br>commitment to helping the <br>weak and needy. Despite her <br>noble background, she never <br>hesitated to get her hands <br>dirty to help her neighbor.<br>Information: During the visit to the city, Abel will <br>approach the Hunters trying to warn them of the <br>disappearance of Bianca Karenmann, which is suspicious <br>to him.<br>Abel the Young Lover<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a young baker who has always been in <br>love with Bianca.<br>Agenda: To find Bianca, as I cannot believe that she has <br>abandoned Lohr, nor that her parents would let her go so <br>easily.<br>Svenn’s House<br>Descriptor: A beautiful manor house, now converted <br>into a museum of hunting trophies.<br>Information: Svenn will greet the Hunters <br>with kindness, boasting that he is the man the <br>Karenmann family trusts the most. Svenn will tell <br>them of the doubts he has about Old Bruna and <br>of the fact that some secrets related to the death <br>of Ottone could be hidden in the woman’s house. <br>Svenn will advise the Hunters to act with caution, <br>so as not to alarm the inhabitants of Lohr, but he <br>will make himself available to distract the woman, <br>driving her away from home with an excuse.</p><p>112<br>Svenn the Skilled Hunter<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the <br>prey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world <br>and I’m used to handling every situation without too many <br>scruples.<br>Agenda: To make Bruna take the blame to divert attention <br>from Bianca / Pretend to help the Hunters to make sure they <br>close the case as quickly as possible.<br>Gift – The Solver:  Svenn takes great care of solving and <br>fixing all the problems of those who offer him a job. Against <br>any attempt at mind control, gathering information, or <br>trying to intimidate him, Svenn’s OL is Hard 7. <br>Bruna’s House<br>Descriptor: A small old house with a <br>garden full of medicinal plants.<br>Information: Bruna lives alone since <br>her husband’s death. Anyone who <br>knows herbs will understand that <br>the woman has good botanical <br>knowledge. Under the bed, <br>Svenn hid a bag with a book of <br>blasphemous rituals and a lock <br>of blond hair that belonged to <br>Ottone.<br>Bruna the Poor Witch<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a poor old woman to whom life has <br>offered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, <br>but I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending <br>up at the stake.<br>Agenda: To live in peace, seeking acceptance from the <br>inhabitants of Lohr.<br>Gift – Latent Witch:  Bruna has magic abilities, but <br>she never studied and uses her powers unconsciously. If <br>threatened, Bruna will activate her power and the objects <br>in the immediate vicinity will begin to move and then fall <br>upon everyone. Acting in the area affected by this power <br>confers 2 Penalties on each Check due to the uncontrolled <br>magic manifestations. If Bruna is killed, she will curse her <br>killer who, for the rest of the Scenario, will receive 1 Penalty <br>at each Defense Check. A practitioner of magic or someone <br>who can communicate with spirits can soothe Bruna’s soul <br>to undo the curse, but a Position Check will be required <br>against an OL Hard 7. <br>The Surroundings of Lohr<br>Descriptor: The village of Lohr stands on the edge of the <br>great Black Forest and is surrounded by many particular and <br>mysterious places.<br>While wandering around Lohr, the Hunters can reach one <br>of the following places. Roll a die (considering the results <br>from 1-3 as 1) or choose based on the information you want <br>to bring into play. If the Hunters move in free exploration, <br>each place is related to a cardinal direction.</p><p>113<br>1. To the North of the village flows a river that the <br>inhabitants use to collect water and fish. Far from <br>prying eyes, every morning, Bianca goes to wash <br>the clothes of the Hessian mercenaries. During the <br>afternoon, you may run into them (see “The escort” <br>on the next column). At night, this is the place <br>where Elsa and Bianca meet for a hug.<br>2. Continuing North (past the river) extends a large <br>area that Svenn uses as a hunting ground. The man <br>has scattered traps in the area and it is often possible <br>to find a dying animal, Svenn not even bothering to <br>put an end to its suffering.<br>Threat – Svenn’s Traps<br>Descriptor: A series of dangerous traps cleverly positioned.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Gift – Alarms:  Svenn’s traps are all designed to cause <br>deep wounds, and failing a Defense Check means suffering <br>1 Wound. In addition, they generate a loud noise that can <br>easily alert the Hessian mercenaries in the mine and warn <br>them against potential intruders. <br>3. Further North, after Svenn’s traps, the Hunters will <br>reach the old mine (see the next column).<br>4. To the West of the village, the Hunters will come <br>across a soldier on horseback traveling to Dresden. <br>The soldier, if questioned, will say that he is bringing <br>a dispatch to the city because seven dangerous war <br>criminals have been seen in the area, fleeing after <br>having killed an officer.<br>5.  To the South, the Hunters will come across a <br>small, abandoned house. Inside, there is a thug called <br>Berno. The man is terrified and, if questioned, he will <br>reveal that, two days earlier, he and his companion <br>Folke tried to take advantage of a beautiful young girl <br>with black hair who was washing military uniforms <br>at the river. When Folke touched the young woman, <br>the man’s body first swelled and then exploded into <br>a pool of blood and guts. Berno then ran for his life, <br>without looking back.<br>6. Traveling East, the Hunters will come to the great <br>road that leads out of the forest. The remains of a <br>camp made by the Hessian mercenaries indicate that <br>someone went to the mine after recovering their <br>strength.<br>The Mine<br>Descriptor: A large, abandoned mine riddled with <br>hundreds of tunnels. Hidden by trees and plants, there is a <br>small building that used to house the head of the excavations.<br>Information: Bianca lives in the small building on the <br>top of the mine, but a tunnel dug by the Hessians allows <br>her to descend into the mine at any time. After Folke and <br>Berno’s attempted aggression, the band of Hessians will <br>divide into two groups:<br> ◆ The escort: Includes Wrath, Corpse, and Grinner. <br>They always follow Bianca when she leaves the mine <br>and will act as a guard in frequent late-night meetings <br>with her mother Elsa.<br> ◆ The guardians: Includes Crucible, Stitch, Shadow, <br>and Rookie. This group is working to turn the mine <br>into a new home, as the mercenaries have decided to <br>settle permanently in Lohr.</p><p>7<br>114<br>Moving around the mine without knowing it is difficult. A <br>map of the area that the mercenaries are renovating can be <br>found in the house where Bianca lives. The map is inside a <br>small chest, with a trap built by Crucible.<br>Threat – Safety Deposit Box<br>Descriptor: A small reinforced wooden box engraved with <br>strange runes.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Gift – Get Your Filthy Hands Away!:  Opening the <br>box by failing the Position Check or without using the <br>password, i.e. beer and prostitutes, causes the activation of a <br>strong electric shock that inflicts 1 Wound and alerts Stitch <br>of the attempt to break in. In this case, increase the Our <br>New Home Gift Trench Tokens by 1.<br>Threat – Mine Tunnels<br>Descriptor: A series of intricate passages that all look alike.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Gift – Our New Home:  Start the Scenario with 2 Trench <br>Tokens on this Gift to represent the defenses put in place <br>by the Hessian mercenaries. For each section of mine <br>traversed, the Storyteller must set up a Scene and the <br>mercenaries can spend 1 Trench Token to activate each of <br>these effects once per Scenario. <br>Note: To reach Bianca in the mines, it is necessary to travel <br>at least 2 sections (3 if the Hessian mercenaries use Escape!).<br>1. Escape!: The screams of the Hessians rumble between <br>the tunnels and Bianca moves away from the Hunters by 1 <br>section. <br>2. Boom!: The mercenaries cause a collapse in the passage, <br>overwhelming the Hunters, who will have to pass a Defense <br>Check against OL Hard 7 not to suffer 1 Wound. <br>3. Screw you!:  One or more mercenaries ambush the <br>Hunters from behind, starting a conflict in which at least <br>two of them act first in the Exchange.<br>4. Lights Out!:  Every source of light is blocked and the <br>Hunters find themselves in total darkness. If Shadow is <br>present, he will take advantage of it to attack the Hunters, <br>possibly taking Didi the Rookie with him. <br>The Seven Hessian Mercenaries<br>Seven skilled mercenaries, united by dwarfism syndrome, who <br>have worked with various military forces. Their condition <br>has always put them on the margins of the army, despite the <br>impressive results they’ve obtained on the battlefield. When <br>Siegbold fell ill, his execution was ordered, but the team <br>rebelled by killing all the officers present. Now the seven <br>mercenaries are wanted for war crimes and desertion.<br>Note: To facilitate the management of a group of 7 NPCs, <br>all mercenaries have the same basic profile. However, <br>everyone has an exclusive Gift that characterizes the <br>way they act. In addition, each mercenary has a different <br>ending for his Descriptor. All mercenaries are ex-soldiers <br>accustomed to war and are armed to face hand-to-hand <br>and ranged opponents. <br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (1 Wound)</p><p>7<br>7<br>7<br>115<br>Descriptor: I am a capable mercenary who has experienced <br>a thousand battles and…[to be completed with the specific <br>Descriptor of each mercenary]<br>Agenda: Protect Bianca to maintain the support of the <br>Karenmann family / Transform the mine into our new home.<br>Dolf called “Crucible”<br>Descriptor: I know alchemy and magic, which I have <br>studied with interest over the years. My glasses are <br>constantly crooked.<br>Gift – Antimagus:  Crucible knows how <br>to create magical interference through <br>the use of vibrations generated by <br>slamming an iron rod on the barrel <br>of his gun. All actions involving <br>the use of spells and magic in his <br>presence receive 1 Penalty.<br>Grimbert called <br>“Wrath”<br>Descriptor: When I <br>get angry, my strength <br>doubles. I chew tobacco all <br>the time.<br>Gift – Warrior’s Fury:  <br>Wrath ignores the first <br>Wound he suffers in each <br>Scene. When he makes <br>an attack, regardless of <br>the outcome, the enemy is <br>overwhelmed by Grimbert’s fury and receives 2 Penalties to <br>their next action.<br>Siegbold called “Corpse”<br>Descriptor: My skin is hard and I have survived many <br>wounds. My body is covered in old, dirty bandages.<br>Gift – Leather Skin:  Corpse can suffer 2 additional <br>Wounds.<br>Bertold called “Stitch”<br>Descriptor: I am a good field doctor. I smell <br>of the alcohol I use to heal wounds and lighten <br>the soul.<br>Gift – It is not the Time to Die, Friend:  <br>Once per Scene, Bertold can heal 1 Wound <br>from a patient which receives care from <br>him. This can also bring someone who has <br>lost their last Wound back into the action. <br>Stani called “Shadow”<br>Descriptor: I am a perfect spy, easily <br>moving through the shadows. I hate <br>sunlight because I suffer from albinism.<br>Gift – Nocturnal:  Stani ignores any <br>penalty derived from effects that reduce <br>the ability to see and perceive an enemy. <br>This also applies to magical shrouds.</p><p>116<br> Didi called “Rookie”<br>Descriptor: I am the youngest in the group and I am good <br>at following orders. I can never stand still, and I speak quickly, <br>words tumbling over each other.<br>Gift – Yes, Sir!: Didi is always where others need him to be. <br>Once per Scene, another mercenary can call Didi to attention, <br>making him appear in the Scene ready to execute any order. <br>Didi can follow a partner in action and imitate his deeds, and <br>thanks to this he can make use of the exclusive Gift of those <br>he is supporting. <br>Hagen called “Grinner”<br>Descriptor: I am good at torture and I know how to make <br>a prisoner talk. A conspicuous scar gives my face a perpetual <br>sneer.<br>Gift – Grim:  Hagen knows how to exploit fear and mind <br>control, so he is completely immune to it. In his presence, his <br>teammates increase their Opposition Level by 1 to resist the <br>effects of fear and mind control.<br>Bianca<br> Karenmann<br>OL Easy 3 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in <br>peace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. <br>It also gives me the power to make living beings explode from <br>within.<br>Agenda: I want what’s best for the whole village of Lohr, even <br>if it means sacrificing myself.<br>Gift – The Curse of Bloodwhite:  Thanks to the power of <br>the curse, Bianca is stronger and more resilient than normal. <br>For this reason, at the end of each Scene she recovers 1 <br>Wound. This effect even allows Bianca to return from <br>death. Bianca’s power can detonate the body of living <br>beings and, once per Exchange, her action can inflict <br>1 automatic Wound to a target. No Defense Check is <br>allowed.</p><p>117<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>If the Hunters pay too much attention to Abel:  <br>Svenn will intervene as soon as possible by making the <br>young man disappear. Abel will be imprisoned in a pit in <br>the hunting ground.<br>If the Hunters capture Bianca: Elsa and Karl will call <br>a public assembly, trying to demonstrate to the Hunters <br>how beloved Bianca is and that she does not deserve to be <br>locked up by the Order.<br>If Bianca sees the people she cares about <br>endangered by the Hunters: she will surrender of her <br>own free will, trying to negotiate for the salvation of those <br>she loves.<br>If the Hunters openly declare that they do not <br>believe Bruna is guilty:  Karl and Elsa will make the <br>Hunters understand that they are no longer welcome in <br>Lohr and they will threaten to write a letter to the Prince <br>to complain.<br>If the Hunters defeat or capture at least three <br>Hessian mercenaries: the other mercenaries will try <br>to start a negotiation with them. It will be clear that, for <br>mercenaries, their comrades come first. <br>The first night after the arrival of the Hunters: Elsa <br>will go to the river with Svenn as her escort to meet Bianca <br>and warn her of the presence of the Hunters. <br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the <br>Bloodwhite’s Heart Scenario and can be acquired once the <br>conditions are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario <br>Gift and if they acquire a new one, they will have to forgo <br>the previous one.<br>Gift – Stake’s Spirit<br>Requirement: Examine the old stakes in the square of <br>Lohr or show interest in the past history of witch-hunting.<br>Y ou are aware of the magical power that resides in the <br>village of Lohr and of the extent of the tragic witch trials <br>it once hosted. Once per Scene, you can open your mind <br>to the spirits of the dead witches. Spend 1 Soma and ask <br>a question about the village, one of the inhabitants, or the <br>surrounding areas. The Storyteller will answer with useful <br>information, but keep in mind that it will be conditioned by <br>the witch’s hatred of this place.<br>Gift – One of Us<br>Requirement: Defeat and spare one or more of the Hessian <br>mercenaries.<br>Y ou defeated the fearsome Hessian mercenaries and <br>earned their respect. Once per Scenario, you can call the <br>team to your rescue, and they will arrive in no time. The <br>Hessian mercenaries will act to help you within their NPC <br>capabilities for the current Scene, and then retreat to start <br>brewing some trouble in your location. This Gift can be <br>maintained in all future Scenarios and does not count <br>towards the maximum of the Gifts you have available.</p><p>1<br>2<br>3a<br>118<br>The Scenario <br>Bloodwhite’s Heart <br>in Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  Arrival in Lohr<br>It’s the same one you find on page 110. After the interview <br>with the Karenmanns, the Hunters go to Svenn to talk about <br>his investigation. Before arriving, Abel will intercept the <br>Hunters, revealing his doubts about Bianca’s departure.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters meet Svenn. Go to THE</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717905,"modifiedTime":1781513717905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qQd4L2k4Xs4zG2cd","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Bloodwhite's Heart - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE – The huntsman.</p><p>SECOND SCENE – The huntsman<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Svenn’s house is a few minutes <br>from the Karenmann palace. With the words of the young Abel <br>still in your head, you find yourself in front of a once lovely <br>mansion. Unfortunately, the trophies of Svenn’s hunting skills <br>spoil its beauty from the entrance: a huge, tacky stuffed bear is <br>placed next to the door. <br>Place: Svenn the huntsman’s house.<br>Time: Mid-morning.<br>Information: Svenn will welcome the Hunters inside <br>the house and will describe everything he has “discovered. ” <br>He’ll also eagerly volunteer to distract Bruna with an excuse, <br>luring her away from her home. When asked about Bianca <br>and Abel, he will say that the young man is the classic loser <br>who fell in love with a girl to whom he should not even speak.<br>End of Scene:  If the Hunters trust Svenn, go to THIRD <br>SCENE OPTION A – Witch hunt , if instead, they decide to <br>search the surroundings of Lohr as requested by Abel, go to</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717905,"modifiedTime":1781513717905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9qlS0o8etHVF6COO","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Bloodwhite's Heart - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B – The river.</p><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>Witch hunt<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Entering Bruna’s small and old <br>house isn’t difficult for you. Apart from an abundant garden <br>full of medicinal herbs, little of what you see qualifies as proof <br>that this is the home of a witch. But, maybe you just have to <br>look more closely...<br>Place: Bruna’s crumbling house.<br>Time: It is late afternoon when Svenn sends for Bruna to ask <br>her for advice on some herbs he found in the woods.<br>Information: Searching the house, it will be easy to discover <br>a bag under the bed, inside of which is a book about magic <br>and a lock of blonde hair. Taking the evidence to Svenn, he <br>will confirm that the hair color is the same as that of Ottone’s <br>and that the young scion kept his hair tied in a tail (which, <br>coincidentally, was cut from the corpse).<br> ◆ If the Hunters have no doubts, Svenn will have Bruna <br>removed from the house, and accuse her of witchcraft. <br>Elsa and Karl will congratulate them on the speed with <br>which they have solved the case. <br> ◆ Convinced or not, Abel will approach the Hunters to <br>tell them he made a macabre discovery as he searched <br>the outskirts of the village for tracks. He’ll make an <br>appointment with them after sundown to avoid Svenn’s <br>attention.</p><p>3b<br>119<br> ◆ If they go along, it will be clear to the Hunters that <br>they are no longer welcome in Lohr, and that from this <br>moment on, their stay is no longer viewed favorably by <br>the Karenmanns.<br>End of Scene: Shortly before sunset, Abel will contact the <br>Hunters saying that some very suspicious deserters have <br>settled at the old mine and that the mine would be a perfect <br>place to keep someone in captivity. Go to THE FOURTH <br>SCENE – The mine.</p><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  <br>The river<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  To the north flows a large <br>river, which separates the inhabited part of the village from <br>the old mine. Abel told you that the mine is now abandoned <br>and that it is often used as a refuge for fleeing deserters and <br>thugs. Your attention is drawn by a melodious voice, a young <br>girl with long black hair is washing military uniforms at the <br>river. Even if you cannot see her well, the resemblance to the <br>daughter of the Karenmanns that you saw in the paintings of <br>the palace is quite striking. Noticing your presence, the young <br>woman flees to the mine while three short, squat men come out <br>of the bush to block your way.<br>Place: The river that flows between the village of Lohr and <br>the abandoned mine.<br>Time: It is early afternoon. <br>Information: The Hessian mercenary escort group (page <br>113) will instruct the Hunters to go somewhere else, making <br>it clear that the mine is now to be considered their property. <br>If they are overwhelmed or outnumbered, the mercenaries <br>will call Rookie for support. However, it is not the intention</p><p>120<br>of the Hessians to enter into conflict with the Hunters and <br>if asked about who the girl is, they will say that it is a young <br>woman from the village whom they pay to do some chores. <br> ◆ If the Hunters get into a fight, Svenn will arrive after <br>one Exchange, trying to put an end to the hostilities. <br>The huntsman will instruct the Hunters not to seek <br>trouble with the group of mercenaries who are “passing <br>through, ” and will tell the mercenaries that they have <br>a day to “get out of the way. ” The Hunters will catch <br>a clear look of understanding between Svenn and the <br>mercenaries.<br> ◆ If the Hunters return to report, both Svenn and the <br>Karenmanns will attempt to divert attention from the <br>mine, prompting the Hunters to investigate Bruna. <br>End of Scene:  If the Hunters trust Svenn, go to THIRD <br>SCENE OPTION A – Witch hunt , if they decide to <br>investigate the girl at the mine, go to FOURTH SCENE – <br>The mine.</p><p>54<br>121</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717905,"modifiedTime":1781513717905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lZT0a3hjj7MZ0Fhl","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Bloodwhite's Heart - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE –  The mine<br>This Scene can be reached in different ways, but once <br>they get to the mine it will be clear to the Hunters that the <br>Hessians keep Bianca Karenmann with them. The mine <br>must be managed as indicated on page 113, taking into <br>account the intentions and strategies of the Hunters.<br>Place: The old abandoned mine near Lohr.<br>Time: The sun is setting.<br>Information:<br> ◆ The Hessians will fight to the death if necessary, but <br>Bianca herself will surrender if the Hunters seem to be <br>getting the better of the situation.<br> ◆ Bianca will confess to everything if faced with the <br>staging that her parents created to save her, especially <br>if this can prevent an innocent woman like Bruna from <br>an unjust accusation.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters retrieve Bianca Karenmann <br>and return to Lohr, go to the FIFTH SCENE – The trial.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717905,"modifiedTime":1781513717905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"F0OwOK4N8CMq8uBm","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Bloodwhite's Heart - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE –  The trial<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you return to Lohr <br>with Bianca, all eyes of the village are on you. The smiles and <br>greetings with which the inhabitants welcome Bianca are a <br>clear sign of how much the daughter of the Karenmanns is <br>loved and esteemed. Arriving at the central square, Elsa and <br>Karl await you with a group of armed guards. There is no <br>hatred in their eyes, but only the concern given by a parent’s <br>love for their daughter.<br>Place: The central square of Lohr, near the old stakes <br>where witches were bound and burned still stands as a <br>warning to all the inhabitants.<br>Time: The sun has just risen, after a night of clashes at the <br>mine.<br>Information: Elsa and Karl will go all-in by asking the <br>Hunters not to imprison their beloved daughter. The two <br>nobles will be supported by the testimonies of the villagers. <br>It will quickly become clear that everyone considers Bianca <br>a pure and kind soul.<br>End of Scene: It will be up to the Hunters to decide the <br>fate of Bianca Karenmann.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717905,"modifiedTime":1781513717905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","collection":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","pages":"109-122"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717905,"modifiedTime":1781513717905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
